<p data-path-to-node="11"> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('40632a28-da8d-4ebf-a802-cc968e139abc', '12a95cdd-47cc-472c-a75e-e2630fb4dfd4', 'radio', 'Questions 11–16', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>MOVING OFFICE</strong></span></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "to have more space"}, {"content": "to pay less rent"}, {"content": "be in a central location"}], "question": "What reason does the manager give for moving to a new office building?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "the air-conditioning system"}, {"content": "the amount of natural light"}, {"content": "the low level of noise"}], "question": "What is best about the new office building?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "after the sales conference"}, {"content": "after the end of the tax year"}, {"content": "after the annual holiday period"}], "question": "When will the office move take place?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "where to park"}, {"content": "places to eat"}, {"content": "public transport"}], "question": "what information about the new location is already on the company website?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "give details of damaged furniture"}, {"content": "throw away unnecessary papers"}, {"content": "take home personal items"}], "question": "What practical thing must staff do now?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "into packing boxes"}, {"content": "into grey plastic bags"}, {"content": "into new filing cabinets"}], "question": "Staff will need to put folders containing confidential details"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a manager talking to company employees about moving to a new office building. First you have some time to look at questions eleven to sixteen. Now listen carefully and answer questions eleven to sixteen.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Người dẫn chuyện:</strong> Bạn sẽ nghe một người quản lý nói chuyện với nhân viên công ty về việc chuyển đến một tòa nhà văn phòng mới. Đầu tiên, bạn có thời gian để xem các câu hỏi 11 đến 16. Bây giờ hãy lắng nghe cẩn thận và trả lời các câu hỏi 11 đến 16.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong>Manager:</strong> Thank you for coming to today’s meeting, everyone. I’d like to give you some information about moving to our new office building so that you know what the plans are. So first, let me explain why we’re moving. Even though we’ve taken on quite a few new employees over the last year, we still have plenty of space here. But the problem is where we are, but we’ve now found the perfect place in the <strong>(11) City Centre</strong> <strong>(C: be in a central location)</strong>. Originally we chose this building in the suburbs because the rent was much cheaper, but our clients aren’t always keen on coming out here.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Quản lý:</strong> Cảm ơn mọi người đã đến cuộc họp hôm nay. Trước hết, tôi xin giải thích lý do chúng ta chuyển văn phòng. Vấn đề là vị trí hiện tại của chúng ta. Chúng ta đã tìm thấy một nơi hoàn hảo ở <strong>(11) Trung tâm Thành phố (C)</strong>. Khách hàng của chúng ta không thích đến đây.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong>Manager:</strong> I visited the new office last week, and I’m pretty sure that you’ll find the greatest advantage is the huge <strong>(12) Windows</strong> <strong>(B: the amount of natural light)</strong>. I’m not sure we’ll need desk lamps at all. Of course, we’ll have everything checked out to make sure we can control the temperature of each office and we may have to put some room dividers in some offices so that you’re not disturbed by your colleagues’ conversations.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> Tôi chắc chắn rằng ưu điểm lớn nhất là những <strong>(12) Cửa sổ</strong> khổng lồ <strong>(B: lượng ánh sáng tự nhiên)</strong>. Tôi không chắc chúng ta sẽ cần đèn bàn.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong>Manager:</strong> We’ve just set a date for the move. The finance department wanted us to wait until after the end of the tax year, April, but we’ve decided to move earlier. As soon as the <strong>(13) sales conference is over in January</strong> <strong>(A: after the sales conference)</strong>, we’ll move. That’ll give us plenty of time to organize everything before you start taking your annual holidays. We’ve already put quite a bit of information about the move on the company website, like <strong>(14) restaurants and cafes</strong> around the new office <strong>(B: places to eat)</strong>. But we’re still checking bus routes and things like that, so transport information will be up by next Monday. Another thing still to get confirmed is which car park we can use and how many people can use it.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> Chúng ta đã ấn định ngày chuyển. Chúng ta sẽ chuyển ngay sau khi <strong>(13) hội nghị bán hàng kết thúc vào tháng Giêng (A)</strong>. Chúng tôi đã đăng thông tin về <strong>(14) nhà hàng và quán cà phê (B)</strong> quanh văn phòng mới lên website công ty.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong>Manager:</strong> Okay, let’s move on to some practical things you have to do now. Don’t worry yet about taking home your photos and things like that, that can be sorted out much nearer the time, along with getting rid of any unwanted paperwork. We need to find out how many new desks and chairs to order so could you make a list of any of the ones you use that are scratched or <strong>(15) broken</strong> <strong>(A: give details of damaged furniture)</strong>. Just one thing, all documents containing non-confidential information can go into the general packing boxes, but when it comes to documents containing confidential information, you’ll need to put these in special bags. You’ll be given <strong>(16) Grey plastic ones</strong> for this <strong>(B: into grey plastic bags)</strong>.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> Bây giờ là một số việc thực tế các bạn phải làm. Các bạn hãy lập danh sách những bàn ghế nào bị trầy xước hoặc <strong>(15) hỏng</strong> <strong>(A: cung cấp chi tiết về đồ nội thất bị hư hỏng)</strong> để chúng ta đặt hàng mới. Đối với tài liệu mật, các bạn sẽ được phát <strong>(16) túi nhựa màu xám (B)</strong> để đựng.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"13\" />\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the talk, you have some time to look at questions seventeen to twenty on page four. Now listen and answer questions seventeen to twenty.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Người dẫn chuyện:</strong> Trước khi bạn nghe phần còn lại của bài nói chuyện, bạn có thời gian để xem các câu hỏi 17 đến 20. Bây giờ hãy lắng nghe và trả lời các câu hỏi 17 đến 20.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong>Manager:</strong> Now to help you prepare for the move, I’d like to talk about lifting heavy things. It’s surprising how often people don’t remember to <strong>(17) use the handles</strong> on the boxes (D: use handles), although they all have them. You’ve all had the leaflet explaining that you should keep your back straight and your head up when lifting, and it also tells you to stand with your feet firmly on the ground and a little bit apart. But the leaflet emphasizes the importance of not <strong>(18) twisting</strong> to the left or right once you’ve picked something up (C: don’t lean to one side). And if you’re like me, that’s easy to forget.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Quản lý:</strong> Về việc nâng vật nặng, thật ngạc nhiên khi mọi người thường quên <strong>(17) sử dụng tay cầm</strong> trên thùng (D). Cẩm nang cũng nhấn mạnh tầm quan trọng của việc không được <strong>(18) xoay người</strong> sang trái hoặc phải khi đã nâng vật lên (C).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong>Manager:</strong> I’d also like to talk about papers. If they’ve been stored for a long time, they may have mold and fungus. As you know, you can’t open the windows in this building, but I suggest you use the <strong>(19) gloves</strong> that we’ll provide (C: wear gloves). We’ll also get some face masks, but we’ve been advised that these shouldn’t be necessary. What you should do is <strong>(20) drink one or two liters of water</strong> a day (D: drink plenty of water). That’s essential. Often the best time to do this sort of work is after your afternoon break so that you can leave the building soon afterwards. Now, are there any questions?</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> Về tài liệu, tôi đề nghị các bạn sử dụng <strong>(19) găng tay</strong> mà chúng tôi cung cấp (C). Điều các bạn nên làm là <strong>(20) uống một hoặc hai lít nước mỗi ngày</strong> (D).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section Two. You now have half a minute to check your answers.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e4210fe2-df9c-4ebe-be60-7c872891140a', '9c83cf93-cf6c-4789-a53c-4079ba88e689', 'matrix', 'Questions 32–35', '', '<p data-start="253" data-end="324">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="279" data-end="286">A–E</strong>, in boxes 32–35 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p data-start="326" data-end="371"><strong data-start="326" data-end="332">NB</strong> You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of options", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Some members of this species have started to contribute more to the care of the young.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "This species avoids areas covered with vegetation when selecting nest sites.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "This species has a favourite flower that it feeds on.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "This species has only been found in Britain in the past few years.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "The banded mining bee", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "The ivy bee", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Andrena scotica", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Lasioglossum malachurum", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "The red mason bee", "categoryLetter": "E"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. Some members of this species have started to contribute more to the care of the young. — {D} Lasioglossum malachurum</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Indeed some of Britain’s solitary bees, <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">Lasioglossum malachurum</strong> for example, are already demonstrating this type of <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">social behaviour</strong>… worker bees <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">sharing care of the grubs</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 7)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết nêu ví dụ cụ thể về loài <em data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">Lasioglossum malachurum</em> đã bắt đầu thể hiện tập tính xã hội, nơi các con ong thợ cùng nhau chăm sóc ấu trùng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"156\">care of the grubs/young</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. This species avoids areas covered with vegetation when selecting nest sites. — {A} The banded mining bee</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">The banded mining bee</strong>… always chooses <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">bare earth</strong> because it <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">doesn’t like having to eat through plant roots</strong> to make its nest.”</em> (Đoạn 5)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Bare earth” (đất trống) chính là những khu vực không có thực vật che phủ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">avoids vegetation</strong>). Loài ong này chọn đất trống vì nó không thích phải đào xuyên qua rễ cây để làm tổ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. This species has a favourite flower that it feeds on. — {A} The banded mining bee</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Females [of the banded mining bee] feed on a variety of plants, but seem <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">particularly fond of yellow dandelions</strong>…”</em> (Đoạn 5)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “particularly fond of” (đặc biệt thích) tương ứng với “favourite flower”. Loài hoa yêu thích của nó là hoa bồ công anh vàng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. This species has only been found in Britain in the past few years. — {B} The ivy bee</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Another bee… is the <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">ivy bee</strong>. It was <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">only identified as a distinct species in 1993</strong>. It is one of a number of bees that have been able to <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"150\">establish themselves in Britain</strong> due to the recent warmer winters.”</em> (Đoạn 6)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> So với lịch sử lâu đời của các loài khác, loài ong ivy mới chỉ được xác định và thiết lập quần thể tại Anh gần đây (tính từ mốc 1993 và các mùa đông ấm áp gần đây).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('01d64cf0-e410-469e-888c-659fd006ce78', '12a95cdd-47cc-472c-a75e-e2630fb4dfd4', 'checkbox', 'Questions 17–18', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>things do people often forget when lifting heavy things?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A keep your head up", "correct": false}, {"option": "B don’t bend your back", "correct": false}, {"option": "C don’t lean to one side", "correct": true}, {"option": "D use handles", "correct": true}, {"option": "E stand with feet apart", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e1ad8726-2d49-47b3-9b81-a7d36a2e467a', '12a95cdd-47cc-472c-a75e-e2630fb4dfd4', 'checkbox', 'Questions 19–20', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>things should staff do when moving papers?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A wear a face mask", "correct": false}, {"option": "B open windows", "correct": false}, {"option": "C wear gloves", "correct": true}, {"option": "D take frequent breaks", "correct": false}, {"option": "E drink plenty of water", "correct": true}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ed71657e-b66b-4a16-ab89-f956894cd8df', 'beff67df-f921-4b68-bc09-8ca8ac8e8684', 'radio', 'Questions 11–16', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B or C.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Moving Office</strong></span></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. to have more space"}, {"content": "B. to pay less rent"}, {"content": "C. be in a central location"}], "question": "What reason does the manager give for moving to a new office building?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. the air-conditioning system "}, {"content": "B. the amount of natural light "}, {"content": "C. the low level of noise"}], "question": "What is best about the new office building?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. after the sales conference "}, {"content": "B. after the end of the tax year "}, {"content": "C. after the annual holiday period"}], "question": "When will the office move take place? "}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. where to park"}, {"content": "B. places to eat "}, {"content": "C. public transport"}], "question": "What information about the new location is already on the company website?  "}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. give details of damaged furniture "}, {"content": "B. throw away unnecessary papers "}, {"content": "C. take home personal items"}], "question": "What practical thing must staff do now? "}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A into packing boxes"}, {"content": "B into grey plastic bags   "}, {"content": "C into new filing cabinets"}], "question": "Staff will need to put folders containing confidential details "}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>Thank you for coming to today&#8217;s meeting everyone. I&#8217;d like to give you some information about moving to our new office building, so that you know what the plans are. So first, let me explain why we&#8217;re moving. Even though we&#8217;ve taken on quite a few new employees over the last year, we still have plenty of space here. But the problem is where we are. We&#8217;ve now found the perfect place in the <strong>(11) city centre (C)</strong>. Originally we chose this building in the suburbs because the rent was much cheaper, but our clients aren&#8217;t always keen on coming out here.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Cảm ơn mọi người đã đến cuộc họp hôm nay. Tôi muốn cung cấp cho các bạn một số thông tin về việc chuyển đến tòa nhà văn phòng mới của chúng ta, để các bạn biết các kế hoạch là gì. Vậy trước tiên, hãy để tôi giải thích lý do tại sao chúng ta chuyển đi. Mặc dù chúng ta đã tuyển thêm khá nhiều nhân viên mới trong năm qua, chúng ta vẫn còn nhiều không gian ở đây. Nhưng vấn đề là nơi chúng ta đang ở. Giờ chúng ta đã tìm thấy một địa điểm hoàn hảo ở <strong>(11) trung tâm thành phố (C)</strong>. Ban đầu chúng ta chọn tòa nhà này ở ngoại ô vì tiền thuê rẻ hơn nhiều, nhưng khách hàng của chúng ta không phải lúc nào cũng nhiệt tình đến đây.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I visited the new office last week and I&#8217;m pretty sure that you&#8217;ll find the greatest advantage is the <strong>(12) huge windows (B)</strong>. I&#8217;m not sure we&#8217;ll need desk lamps at all. Of course, we&#8217;ll have everything checked out to make sure we can control the temperature of each office, and we may have to put some room dividers in some offices so that you&#8217;re not disturbed by your colleague&#8217;s conversations.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Tôi đã đến thăm văn phòng mới vào tuần trước và tôi khá chắc chắn rằng các bạn sẽ thấy lợi thế lớn nhất là những <strong>(12) cửa sổ lớn (B)</strong>. Tôi không chắc chúng ta sẽ cần đèn bàn nữa. Tất nhiên, chúng ta sẽ kiểm tra mọi thứ để đảm bảo có thể kiểm soát nhiệt độ của từng văn phòng, và chúng ta có thể phải lắp đặt một số vách ngăn trong một số văn phòng để các bạn không bị làm phiền bởi các cuộc trò chuyện của đồng nghiệp.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>We&#8217;ve just set a date for the move. The finance department wanted us to wait until after the end of the tax year (April), but we&#8217;ve decided to move earlier, as soon as the <strong>(13) sales conference is over (A)</strong> in January. We&#8217;ll move then. That&#8217;ll give us plenty of time to organise everything before you start taking your annual holidays.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Chúng ta vừa ấn định ngày chuyển đi. Bộ phận tài chính muốn chúng ta đợi đến sau cuối năm tài chính (tháng Tư), nhưng chúng ta đã quyết định chuyển đi sớm hơn, ngay sau khi <strong>(13) hội nghị bán hàng kết thúc (A)</strong> vào tháng Giêng. Chúng ta sẽ chuyển vào lúc đó. Điều đó sẽ cho chúng ta nhiều thời gian để tổ chức mọi thứ trước khi các bạn bắt đầu nghỉ phép hàng năm.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>We&#8217;ve already put quite a bit of information about the move on the company website, like <strong>(14) restaurants and cafes (B)</strong> around the new office, but we&#8217;re still checking bus routes and things like that, so transport information will be up by next Monday. Another thing still to get confirmed is which car park we can use and how many people can use it.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Chúng ta đã đưa khá nhiều thông tin về việc chuyển đi lên trang web của công ty, chẳng hạn như <strong>(14) nhà hàng và quán cà phê (B)</strong> xung quanh văn phòng mới, nhưng chúng ta vẫn đang kiểm tra các tuyến xe buýt và những thứ tương tự, vì vậy thông tin giao thông sẽ được cập nhật vào thứ Hai tới. Một điều khác vẫn cần được xác nhận là bãi đậu xe nào chúng ta có thể sử dụng và bao nhiêu người có thể sử dụng nó.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Okay, let&#8217;s move on to some practical things you have to do now. Don&#8217;t worry yet about taking home your photos and things like that; that can be sorted out much nearer the time, along with getting rid of any unwanted paperwork. We need to find out how many new desks and chairs to order, so <strong>(15) could you make a list of any of the ones you use that are scratched or broken (A)</strong>. Just one thing: all documents containing non-confidential information can go into the general packing boxes. But when it comes to documents containing confidential information, you&#8217;ll need to put these in special bags. You&#8217;ll be given <strong>(16) grey plastic ones (B)</strong> for this. So, one thing to do now is go through your filing cabinets and identify which folders are confidential.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Được rồi, hãy chuyển sang một số việc thực tế mà các bạn phải làm ngay bây giờ. Đừng lo lắng về việc mang ảnh và những thứ tương tự về nhà vội; việc đó có thể được giải quyết gần ngày chuyển hơn, cùng với việc loại bỏ bất kỳ giấy tờ không cần thiết nào. Chúng ta cần biết phải đặt mua bao nhiêu bàn và ghế mới, vì vậy <strong>(15) các bạn có thể lập danh sách bất kỳ món đồ nào các bạn đang sử dụng bị trầy xước hoặc hư hỏng không (A)</strong>. Chỉ một điều: tất cả các tài liệu không chứa thông tin mật có thể cho vào các hộp đóng gói chung. Nhưng đối với các tài liệu chứa thông tin mật, các bạn sẽ cần cho chúng vào các túi đặc biệt. Các bạn sẽ được cung cấp <strong>(16) túi nhựa màu xám (B)</strong> cho việc này. Vì vậy, một việc cần làm bây giờ là xem qua các tủ đựng hồ sơ của bạn và xác định thư mục nào là mật.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the talk, you have some time to look at questions 17 to 20 on page four. Now listen and answer questions 17 to twenty.</p>\n<p>Now to help you prepare for the move, I&#8217;d like to talk about lifting heavy things. You shouldn&#8217;t really have to do this, because a removal company will be used, but you might want to move a box out of your way or something. It&#8217;s surprising how often people don&#8217;t remember to <strong>(18) use the handles (D)</strong> on the boxes, although they all have them. You&#8217;ve all had the leaflet explaining that you should keep your back straight and your head up when lifting, and it also tells you to stand with your feet firmly on the ground and a little bit apart, so I think that&#8217;s clear. But the leaflet emphasises the importance of <strong>(17) not twisting to the left or right (C)</strong> once you&#8217;ve picked something up, and if you&#8217;re like me, that&#8217;s easy to forget.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Bây giờ để giúp các bạn chuẩn bị cho việc di chuyển, tôi muốn nói về việc nâng vật nặng. Các bạn không cần phải làm điều này, vì sẽ có công ty vận chuyển, nhưng đôi khi các bạn có thể muốn di chuyển một chiếc hộp ra khỏi đường đi hoặc gì đó. Thật đáng ngạc nhiên khi mọi người thường quên <strong>(18) sử dụng tay cầm (D)</strong> trên các thùng, mặc dù tất cả chúng đều có. Tất cả các bạn đã có tờ rơi giải thích rằng các bạn nên giữ lưng thẳng và đầu ngẩng cao khi nâng, và nó cũng nói với các bạn rằng phải đứng hai chân vững chãi trên mặt đất và hơi tách ra, vì vậy tôi nghĩ điều đó rõ ràng. Nhưng tờ rơi nhấn mạnh tầm quan trọng của việc <strong>(17) không xoắn sang trái hoặc phải (C)</strong> một khi bạn đã nhấc vật lên, và nếu bạn giống tôi, điều đó rất dễ quên.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I&#8217;d also like to talk about papers. If they&#8217;ve been stored for a long time, they can get mould on them—a sort of fungus—and as soon as you start moving them, the fungus gets disturbed. As you know, you can&#8217;t open the windows in this building, but I suggest you use the <strong>(19) gloves (C)</strong> that we&#8217;ll provide. We&#8217;ll also get some face masks, but we&#8217;ve been advised that these shouldn&#8217;t be necessary. What you should do is drink one or two litres of water a day; that&#8217;s essential. Often the best time to do this sort of work is after your afternoon break, so that you can leave the building soon afterwards. <strong>(20) (D)</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Tôi cũng muốn nói về giấy tờ. Nếu chúng được lưu trữ lâu ngày, chúng có thể bị mốc—một loại nấm—và ngay khi các bạn bắt đầu di chuyển chúng, nấm sẽ bị khuấy động. Như các bạn biết, các bạn không thể mở cửa sổ trong tòa nhà này, nhưng tôi khuyên các bạn nên sử dụng <strong>(19) găng tay (C)</strong> mà chúng tôi sẽ cung cấp. Chúng tôi cũng sẽ chuẩn bị một số khẩu trang, nhưng chúng tôi được khuyên rằng những thứ này không cần thiết. Điều các bạn nên làm là uống một hoặc hai lít nước mỗi ngày; điều đó rất cần thiết. Thời điểm tốt nhất để thực hiện loại công việc này thường là <strong>(20) sau giờ giải lao buổi chiều (D)</strong>, để các bạn có thể rời khỏi tòa nhà ngay sau đó.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Now, are there any questions?</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section 2. You now have half a minute to check your answers. Now turn to Section 3 on page five.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('19e23157-d6cf-47f9-9cf7-e1ecf3ab03ee', '9c83cf93-cf6c-4789-a53c-4079ba88e689', 'fillup', 'Questions 36–40', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 36–40 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong><span role="text">The life of the solitary bee</span></strong></span></p>
<p>Female solitary bees make their nests with separate {cells}, where single eggs are deposited. Females try to ensure the survival of their {grubs}. They do this by providing suitable food in what is referred to as a {parcel}. Solitary bees use a range of substances to make their nests comfortable and secure, such as plant material or {mud}.</p>
<p>Although some solitary bees are common, certain species are thought to be {rare}. The different solitary bees vary widely in their distribution, some being found all over Britain while others are much more restricted geographically.</p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. Female solitary bees make their nests with separate {cells}, where single eggs are deposited.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“A female solitary bee constructs a nest and then lays her eggs in <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">individual cells</strong>…”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Separate” (tách biệt) đồng nghĩa với “individual” (riêng lẻ). Những quả trứng được đặt vào các ô ngăn cách gọi là các tế bào/ô lưới (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">cells</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. Females try to ensure the survival of their {grubs}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…lining or sealing them with various materials… for each of her <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">little grubs</strong> to feed on.”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mục đích của việc làm tổ và để lại thức ăn là để nuôi dưỡng và đảm bảo sự sống sót cho các ấu trùng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">grubs</strong>) của chúng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. They do this by providing suitable food in what is referred to as a {parcel}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The female leaves what naturalists call a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">‘parcel’</strong> of pollen and nectar…”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nêu rõ tên gọi mà các nhà tự nhiên học đặt cho phần thức ăn dự trữ này là một “bưu kiện” (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">parcel</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. Solitary bees use a range of substances… such as plant material or {mud}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…lining or sealing them with various materials… red mason bees use <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">mud</strong>; leafcutter bees use sections of leaf.”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Plant material” (vật liệu thực vật) tương ứng với “sections of leaf”. Chất liệu còn lại được nhắc tới để xây tổ là bùn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">mud</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. Although some solitary bees are common, certain species are thought to be {rare}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“While some bees are plentiful and widespread, others have been designated as <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">rare</strong>…”</em> (Đoạn 5)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Common” (phổ biến) đối lập với “plentiful and widespread”. “Certain species” (một số loài nhất định) tương ứng với “others”. Từ cần điền là hiếm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"159\">rare</strong>).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5830aa83-4663-4b87-9b6f-229931965ad6', 'beff67df-f921-4b68-bc09-8ca8ac8e8684', 'checkbox', 'Questions 17 - 18', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO</strong> letters, A–E</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>things do people often forget when lifting heavy things?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A. keep your head up ", "correct": false}, {"option": "B. don’t bend your back ", "correct": false}, {"option": "C. don’t lean to one side ", "correct": true}, {"option": "D. use handles ", "correct": true}, {"option": "E. stand with feet apart", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c55f8a88-3e66-482f-b892-54a85fbea276', 'f48a1079-c3aa-448e-bccd-c9f175b27a12', 'fillup', 'Questions 14-17', '<p>Complete the summary below.<br />
Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.<br />
Write your answers in boxes on your answer sheet.</p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;"> Malaria in 19th-century Italy</h3>
<p style="text-align: left;">Up until the late nineteenth century, experts failed to make the connection between malaria and  {insects} The most popular belief at the time was the  {miasma} theory, which upheld the idea that diseases were carried by unclean air. Another common idea was that malaria was a  {Hereditary} disease, and as a result people from certain parts of the country were often held responsible for the spread of epidemics. Malaria was particularly widespread in rural regions, where  {Life expectancy} could be extremely short.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-start=\"137\" data-end=\"158\"><strong data-start=\"141\" data-end=\"156\">14. insects</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"159\" data-end=\"395\">(Đoạn B: “Others made a link between swamps, water and malaria, but did not make the further leap towards <em data-start=\"265\" data-end=\"274\">insects</em>.”)<br data-start=\"277\" data-end=\"280\" />→ Trước cuối thế kỷ 19, các chuyên gia <strong data-start=\"319\" data-end=\"378\">chưa nhận ra mối liên hệ giữa bệnh sốt rét và côn trùng</strong>, cụ thể là muỗi.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"397\" data-end=\"400\" />\n<h3 data-start=\"402\" data-end=\"422\"><strong data-start=\"406\" data-end=\"420\">15. miasma</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"423\" data-end=\"626\">(Đoạn B: “Most experts subscribed to the theory of ‘<em data-start=\"475\" data-end=\"483\">miasma</em>’ or ‘poisoning of the air’.”)<br data-start=\"513\" data-end=\"516\" />→ Lý thuyết phổ biến lúc bấy giờ là <em data-start=\"552\" data-end=\"560\">miasma</em> – cho rằng <strong data-start=\"572\" data-end=\"625\">bệnh lây lan qua không khí bẩn hoặc không khí độc</strong>.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"628\" data-end=\"631\" />\n<h3 data-start=\"633\" data-end=\"657\"><strong data-start=\"637\" data-end=\"655\">16. hereditary</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"658\" data-end=\"917\">(Đoạn B: “Epidemics were blamed on people who originated from the hotter parts of Italy, giving the widespread belief that malaria was <em data-start=\"793\" data-end=\"805\">hereditary</em>.”)<br data-start=\"808\" data-end=\"811\" />→ Người ta tin rằng <strong data-start=\"831\" data-end=\"860\">sốt rét là bệnh di truyền</strong>, nên những người đến từ vùng nóng bị đổ lỗi gây ra dịch.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"919\" data-end=\"922\" />\n<h3 data-start=\"924\" data-end=\"953\"><strong data-start=\"928\" data-end=\"951\">17. life expectancy</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"954\" data-end=\"1202\">(Đoạn B: “In warm, damp, malarial zones, the <em data-start=\"999\" data-end=\"1016\">life expectancy</em> of land workers was a terrifying 22.5 years.”)<br data-start=\"1063\" data-end=\"1066\" />→ Ở vùng nông thôn ẩm ướt, <strong data-start=\"1093\" data-end=\"1155\">tuổi thọ trung bình của người lao động chỉ khoảng 22,5 năm</strong> – minh chứng cho mức độ nghiêm trọng của bệnh.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>➡ Paragraph B: “…subscribed to the theory of ‘miasma’ or ‘poisoning of the air’”<br />\nThis was the most popular belief, that disease came from bad air.<br />\n✅ Answer: miasma</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>➡ Paragraph B: “…the widespread belief that malaria was hereditary.”<br />\nPeople believed malaria was a hereditary disease passed down in families.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>➡ Paragraph B: “…the life expectancy of land workers was a terrifying 22.5 years.”<br />\nThe average lifespan in malarial areas was very short.<br />\n✅ Answer: life expectancy</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ff013c6d-c2ce-46dc-beea-a4d7dfbbba05', 'f48a1079-c3aa-448e-bccd-c9f175b27a12', 'radio', 'Questions 18-20', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The volunteers in Giovanni Battista Grassi’s research came from all parts of Italy."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Experiments in Italy proved that it was possible to remain healthy despite being in malarial zones."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In the early twentieth century, quinine was successfully administered to all inhabitants of vulnerable regions."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>18 NOT GIVEN<br />\n(Đoạn C: “By releasing mosquitoes into rooms with the blood of healthy human volunteers, Grassi was able to show a direct link between the insects and the disease.”)<br />\n→ Đoạn văn chỉ nói rằng có các tình nguyện viên khỏe mạnh tham gia nghiên cứu, không hề đề cập họ đến từ những vùng nào của nước Ý.</p>\n<p>19 TRUE<br />\n(Đoạn C: “Healthy people were introduced into malarial zones but kept free of mosquito bites — and remained well.”)<br />\n→ Thí nghiệm chứng minh rằng con người vẫn có thể khỏe mạnh khi ở trong vùng sốt rét, miễn là tránh được việc bị muỗi đốt.</p>\n<p>20 FALSE<br />\n(Đoạn E: “It was originally decided to give quinine to all those in vulnerable regions… However, peasants were often suspicious… and doctors were frequently met with hostility and stubborn refusal.”)<br />\n→ Ban đầu có kế hoạch phát quinine cho toàn bộ cư dân vùng dễ mắc bệnh, nhưng nhiều người dân không hợp tác, từ chối điều trị → nên không thể nói là được phân phát thành công cho tất cả mọi người.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>➡ Paragraph C: “…people were introduced into malarial zones but kept free of mosquito bites – and remained well.”<br />\nThis proves that people could stay healthy even in malarial areas, if protected.<br />\n✅ Answer: TRUE</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>➡ Paragraph E: “Peasants were often suspicious of medicine… refusal to accept treatment…”<br />\nNot everyone received quinine successfully, especially in rural areas.<br />\n✅ Answer: FALSE</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('aa5be685-3fda-414c-b43e-905a636e32cd', 'f48a1079-c3aa-448e-bccd-c9f175b27a12', 'matrix', 'Questions 21-26', NULL, '<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?<br />
Choose the correct letter, A–H</p>
', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "a figure showing the dramatic results of an anti-malarial drug programme", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "an important discovery about how malaria is spread", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "mention of an expert’s decision not to halt the spread of the disease", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "the significance of the malaria story for today’s readers", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "examples of false assumptions which held back scientific understanding of malaria", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "a reference to legislation to support the fight against malaria", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<h3 data-start=\"131\" data-end=\"221\"><strong data-start=\"135\" data-end=\"219\">21. E — a figure showing the dramatic results of an anti-malarial drug programme</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"223\" data-end=\"556\">(Đoạn E: “Deaths from malaria fell by some 80% in the first decade of the 20th century and some areas escaped altogether from the scourge of the disease.”)<br data-start=\"378\" data-end=\"381\" />→ Đoạn này nêu <strong data-start=\"396\" data-end=\"462\">số liệu cụ thể về hiệu quả của chương trình dùng thuốc quinine</strong>, cho thấy <strong data-start=\"473\" data-end=\"503\">tỷ lệ tử vong giảm tới 80%</strong>, minh họa kết quả đáng kinh ngạc của chương trình.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"558\" data-end=\"561\" />\n<h3 data-start=\"563\" data-end=\"631\"><strong data-start=\"567\" data-end=\"629\">22. C — an important discovery about how malaria is spread</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"633\" data-end=\"933\">(Đoạn C: “The zoologist Giovanni Battista Grassi demonstrated that the micro-organisms causing the disease were carried in the digestive tract of the mosquito.”)<br data-start=\"794\" data-end=\"797\" />→ Đây là <strong data-start=\"806\" data-end=\"882\">phát hiện quan trọng xác định muỗi là vật trung gian truyền bệnh sốt rét</strong>, mở đường cho các biện pháp phòng chống sau này.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"935\" data-end=\"938\" />\n<h3 data-start=\"940\" data-end=\"1027\"><strong data-start=\"944\" data-end=\"1025\">23. F — mention of an expert’s decision not to halt the spread of the disease</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"1029\" data-end=\"1367\">(Đoạn F: “&#8230;the country’s leading malariologist Alberto Missiroli refused to order the distribution of quinine, so allowing the epidemic to spread unchecked.”)<br data-start=\"1189\" data-end=\"1192\" />→ Đoạn này nói rõ <strong data-start=\"1210\" data-end=\"1276\">một chuyên gia (Missiroli) đã cố tình không phát thuốc quinine</strong>, dẫn đến dịch bệnh lan rộng — chính là “quyết định không ngăn chặn sự lây lan của bệnh.”</p>\n<hr data-start=\"1369\" data-end=\"1372\" />\n<h3 data-start=\"1374\" data-end=\"1449\"><strong data-start=\"1378\" data-end=\"1447\">24. H — the significance of the malaria story for today’s readers</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"1451\" data-end=\"1748\">(Đoạn H: “As there are still more than 1m deaths every year from malaria worldwide, Snowden’s book also has contemporary relevance.”)<br data-start=\"1584\" data-end=\"1587\" />→ Đoạn này liên hệ câu chuyện <strong data-start=\"1617\" data-end=\"1685\">về ý nghĩa của cuộc chiến chống sốt rét đối với độc giả hiện nay</strong>, chứng minh nó vẫn còn <strong data-start=\"1709\" data-end=\"1746\">tính thời sự và giá trị nhân văn.</strong></p>\n<hr data-start=\"1750\" data-end=\"1753\" />\n<h3 data-start=\"1755\" data-end=\"1854\"><strong data-start=\"1759\" data-end=\"1852\">25. B — examples of false assumptions which held back scientific understanding of malaria</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"1856\" data-end=\"2191\">(Đoạn B: “Most experts subscribed to the theory of ‘miasma’&#8230; Others made a link between swamps, water and malaria, but did not make the further leap towards insects.”)<br data-start=\"2025\" data-end=\"2028\" />→ Đoạn này mô tả <strong data-start=\"2045\" data-end=\"2073\">những giả thuyết sai lầm</strong> (miasma, di truyền, không khí độc&#8230;) khiến <strong data-start=\"2118\" data-end=\"2189\">khoa học chậm tiến trong việc hiểu nguyên nhân thật sự của sốt rét.</strong></p>\n<hr data-start=\"2193\" data-end=\"2196\" />\n<h3 data-start=\"2198\" data-end=\"2279\"><strong data-start=\"2202\" data-end=\"2277\">26. D — a reference to legislation to support the fight against malaria</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"2281\" data-end=\"2556\">(Đoạn D: “Italy introduced a quinine law and a quinine tax in 1904, and the drug was administered to large numbers of rural workers.”)<br data-start=\"2415\" data-end=\"2418\" />→ Đoạn này nêu <strong data-start=\"2433\" data-end=\"2452\">luật về quinine</strong> được ban hành để hỗ trợ chiến dịch phòng chống sốt rét — chính là “legislation to support the fight.”</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>➡ Paragraph C explains Grassi’s breakthrough discovery: that mosquitoes transmit malaria.<br />\n✅ Answer: C</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>➡ Paragraph F: “Italy’s leading malariologist… refused to order the distribution of quinine…”<br />\nThis deliberate refusal allowed the epidemic to worsen.<br />\n✅ Answer: F</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>➡ Paragraph H: “This magnificent study… has contemporary relevance…”<br />\nIt reflects on why the story is important even today.<br />\n✅ Answer: H</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>➡ Paragraph B includes mistaken ideas like miasma and heredity, which delayed real action.<br />\n✅ Answer: B</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>➡ Paragraph D: “Italy introduced a quinine law…”<br />\nThis is a legal measure taken to combat malaria.<br />\n✅ Answer: D</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1e907c00-ea07-4a70-8843-60ed89b22f05', '83ae0844-3dd2-44ee-afc5-6a45d730600d', 'matrix', 'Questions 27–32', NULL, '<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>F</strong>, in boxes <strong>27-32.<br /></strong></p>
<p><em><strong>NB </strong>You may use any letter more than once.</em></p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Reasons why watching sport can bring emotional satisfaction", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "An explanation of why beginners struggle with sports tasks", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "A factor that can work alongside mirroring in sports competitions to maintain peak performance", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "A comparison between the mirror neurons of human beings and primates", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Mention of integrating visual and motor processes to understand athletic movements", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Reference to the first discovery of brain activity associated with mirror neurons", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>27. reasons why watching sport can bring emotional satisfaction</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: F</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “Most spectators tune in for the <strong>emotional roller coaster</strong>… This emotional connection finds its roots in mirror neurons, which allow spectators to perceive athletes’ victorious movements and to <strong>share in the emotion of their triumphs</strong>.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>28. an explanation of why beginners struggle with sports tasks</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: B</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “…for novices, smoothly manoeuvring the asymmetrical metal club presents a nearly impossible challenge. This is because <strong>novices rely on conscious effort</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc dựa vào nỗ lực có ý thức (conscious effort) khiến người mới (novices) gặp khó khăn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>29. a factor that can work alongside mirroring in sports competitions to maintain peak performance</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: E</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “The most accomplished athletes possess a premotor cortex capable of <strong>envisioning victorious movements</strong> [imagination], supplemented by the physical attributes required to translate those movements into reality. In this way, action and <strong>imagination coalesce to drive performance</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khả năng hình dung (imagination) kết hợp với hành động thúc đẩy hiệu suất.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>30. a comparison between the mirror neurons of human beings and primates</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: C</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “They point out that mirror neurons are activated when a <strong>primate</strong> performs a particular action… <strong>Humans possess an even more intricate</strong> mitor neuron system that reflects the external world in our brains…”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>31. mention of integrating visual and motor processes to understand athletic movements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: E</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “They asserted that to comprehend the movements of sports stars, we need to <strong>align the visual representation of the observed action with our own motor representation</strong> of the same action.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>32. reference to the first discovery of brain activity associated with mirror neurons</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: D</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “This neural mirroring was <strong>initially identified in 1954</strong> by French physiologists Gastaut and Bert, who noticed specific alpha and mu brain wave patterns in humans.”</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('59775db4-ed83-4711-8cee-76aadc01ec6e', 'e4d7277c-5515-4b80-8654-55b8123a5fea', 'matrix', ' Questions 14–19', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 2 has seven paragraphs, <strong>A-G</strong>.</p>
<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": " a finding that humans can distinguish between two extremely similar substances", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "a categorisation of species according to their sensitivity to smell", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "an instance where smell negatively affected people''s ability to make choices", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "a study that proved humans could perceive a tiny quantity of a substance", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "an observation that studies of the sense of smell have been undervalued", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "an example of using smell to prompt people to buy something", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 14</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">D</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “We are also exceptionally gifted at telling smells apart, even in the case of <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">two molecules</strong> whose only difference is that their structures are <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"155\">mirror images</strong> of one another.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc phân biệt được hai phân tử là “hình ảnh phản chiếu” (mirror images) của nhau minh chứng cho khả năng phân biệt hai chất cực kỳ giống nhau (extremely similar substances).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 15</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">B</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…he suggested that mammals can be classed into two broad groups: <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">microsmatic mammals</strong>, such as dogs… while we… are <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"132\">microsmatic</strong> [sic – microsmatic/macrosmatic confusion in original text logic]…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Pierre Paul Broca đã thực hiện phân loại (categorisation) các loài động vật thành hai nhóm dựa trên độ nhạy bén về khứu giác của chúng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 16</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">F</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…when men were subjected to a novel smell… during a task used to test <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">decision-making skills</strong>, they performed <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">significantly worse than normal</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nghiên cứu của William Overman cho thấy mùi hương làm giảm hiệu quả thực hiện các nhiệm vụ đòi hỏi kỹ năng đưa ra quyết định (make choices).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 17</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">C</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “One study, for example, found that we can detect certain chemicals diluted in water to <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">less than one part per billion</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Less than one part per billion” (ít hơn một phần tỷ) tương ứng với một lượng chất cực nhỏ (a tiny quantity of a substance).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 18</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">A</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Noses have certainly <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">never been at the forefront</strong> of sensory research, and were <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">pushed aside until recently</strong> in favour of the seemingly more vital senses of vision and hearing.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc bị “đẩy sang một bên” và “không bao giờ ở vị trí hàng đầu” cho thấy các nghiên cứu về khứu giác đã bị đánh giá thấp (undervalued).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 19</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">E</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…estate agents, who often advocate the smell of baking bread or brewing coffee to <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">promote the sale of a house</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc dùng mùi bánh mì hay cà phê để thúc đẩy việc bán nhà là ví dụ về dùng mùi hương để kích thích mọi người mua hàng (buy something).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('505ff168-b336-48bc-b1e2-df04b804d3f8', 'e4d7277c-5515-4b80-8654-55b8123a5fea', 'matrix', 'Questions 20–23', NULL, '<p>Look at the following statements (Questions 20-23) and the list of people below.</p>
<p>Match each statement with the correct person, <strong>A-F</strong>.</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of people", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "A faint smell could motivate people to do household chores", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Humans are better equipped to interpret smell than other species are", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Smell is associated with feelings, rather than the logical part of the brain", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Humans do not require a sophisticated ability to smell", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Liliane Mujica-parodi", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Pierre Paul Broca", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Charles Greer", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": " Hendrick Schifferstein and colleagues", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "Rob Holland", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "William Overman and colleagues", "categoryLetter": "F"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 20</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">E (Rob Holland)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Meanwhile, <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"23\">Rob Holland</strong>… found that the hint of aroma wafting out of a hidden bucket of citrus-scented cleaner was enough to persuade students… to <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">clean up after themselves</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hành động “dọn dẹp” (clean up) tương ứng với làm việc nhà (household chores).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 21</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">C (Charles Greer)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…<strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">Charles Greer</strong>… has shown that the human nose and brain are <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">unusually well connected</strong>, with each group of receptors linking to many more neural regions than is the case in other animals.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự kết nối “tốt một cách bất thường” giữa mũi và não người so với các động vật khác cho thấy con người được trang bị tốt hơn để giải thích/xử lý mùi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 22</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">F (William Overman and colleagues)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…<strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">William Overman</strong>… The researchers conclude the scent stimulated brain areas <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">connected with emotion</strong>, making their decisions <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">emotional rather than rational</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Kết luận này chỉ ra mùi hương liên quan đến cảm xúc hơn là phần logic/duy lý (rational part) của não bộ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 23</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">B (Pierre Paul Broca)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “<strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Pierre Paul Broca</strong>… suggested that mammals can be classed into two broad groups… [humans] have small olfactory organs that we <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">only rely on to a small extent</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Quan điểm của Broca cho rằng con người chỉ dựa vào khứu giác ở mức độ nhỏ, nghĩa là không yêu cầu một khả năng ngửi tinh vi/phức tạp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6f4f724a-151b-491c-9444-c7a0f8a08ef6', 'e4d7277c-5515-4b80-8654-55b8123a5fea', 'fillup', 'Questions 24–26', '<p>Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>The {Amygdala} is a part of the brain that deals with feeling and smell.</p>
<p>{Unpleasant} smells create especially powerful associations with memories.</p>
<p>Of all the senses, smell has the capacity to prompt memories of {Childhood} .</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 24</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">Amygdala</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…there are certain brain areas dedicated to <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">both emotion and olfaction</strong>, such as the <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">amygdala</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Amygdala là phần não chuyên biệt cho cả cảm xúc (feeling) và khứu giác (smell).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 25</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">Unpleasant</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the link between a memory and a smell is stronger if the smell is <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">unpleasant</strong> rather than pleasant.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mùi “không dễ chịu” tạo ra sự liên kết với ký ức mạnh mẽ hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 26</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">Childhood</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…this explains why smells often transport us back to our <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">childhood</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định mùi hương có khả năng gợi lại những ký ức từ thời thơ ấu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a3c20e20-b5ff-4846-bcac-9b0c2b5a15a1', 'fc24b3a2-01e0-4823-8c24-2f07ed60cc63', 'fillup', 'Questions 1-6', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="33">NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 1-6 on your answer sheet.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9989%; height: 582.207px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 2px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 17.2293%;"> <col style="width: 82.7727%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 33.6133px;">
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><strong>Period</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><strong>Key developments</strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 53.2031px;">
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;">
<p style="text-align: center;">1600s</p>
</td>
<td style="text-align: left; border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Early inventors like Papin started to develop boats that relied on steam instead of manpower or wind.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 53.2031px;">
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;">
<p>1730s</p>
</td>
<td style="text-align: left; border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<ul>
<li>
<p>The engine of Jonathan Hulls’ steamboat was {inefficient} due to its weight.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 153.926px;">
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;">
<p>1780s</p>
</td>
<td style="text-align: left; border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<ul>
<li>
<p>A French paddle steamer did not have the {endurance} to keep going for more than a quarter of an hour.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>John Fitch overcame a number of {technical} problems with his steamboat designs.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 235.059px;">
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;">
<p style="text-align: center;">Early 1800s</p>
</td>
<td style="text-align: left; border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<ul>
<li data-path-to-node="4,4,1,0">
<p>The <em data-path-to-node="4,4,1,0" data-index-in-node="6">Charlotte Dundas</em> pulled barges to Glasgow.</p>
</li>
<li data-path-to-node="4,4,1,2">
<p>In France, Fulton used a steamboat to try to raise interest in a {submarine}.</p>
</li>
<li data-path-to-node="4,4,1,4">
<p>Passengers in the US began to be carried regularly by a steamboat called the {Clermont}</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 53.2031px;">
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;">
<p>1812 onwards</p>
</td>
<td style="text-align: left; border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<ul>
<li>
<p>In Scotland, steamboats transported some passengers, but mostly {cargo}</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. {inefficient} (Thập kỷ 1730)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Englishman Jonathan Hulls took out patents on a steamboat in 1736, but it was to be driven by a Newcomen engine, which was heavy and therefore <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">inefficient</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Động cơ Newcomen mà Jonathan Hulls sử dụng quá nặng, dẫn đến việc nó không hiệu quả (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">inefficient</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. {endurance} (Thập kỷ 1780)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Nearly 20 years later, in the 1780s, a steam-powered paddle-wheeler managed to last fifteen minutes… but lacked the <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">endurance</strong> for longer trips.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Fifteen minutes” (15 phút) tương ứng với “a quarter of an hour” trong đề bài. Con tàu này không đủ sức bền (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">endurance</strong>) để đi những chuyến dài hơn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. {technical} (Thập kỷ 1780)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…John Fitch successfully trialled his first steamboat in 1787, but although he tried a number of designs and solved many <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">technical</strong> challenges…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong đề bài dùng từ “problems”, trong bài đọc dùng “challenges”. John Fitch đã giải quyết được nhiều vấn đề/thách thức về mặt kỹ thuật (<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"149\">technical</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. {submarine} (Đầu những năm 1800)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Fulton ran steamboat trials on the River Seine, in an attempt to attract French support for his <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">submarine</strong> Nautilus.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “raise interest” tương ứng với “attract support”. Robert Fulton trình diễn tàu hơi nước tại Pháp thực chất là để thu hút sự chú ý/ủng hộ cho dự án tàu ngầm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"173\">submarine</strong>) của mình.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. {Clermont} (Đầu những năm 1800)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In 1807, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">Clermont</strong> began a scheduled passenger steamboat service between New York and Albany…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tên con tàu hơi nước đầu tiên thực hiện dịch vụ chở khách định kỳ (scheduled/regularly) tại Mỹ là <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">Clermont</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. {cargo} (Từ năm 1812 trở đi)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…carrying <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">cargo</strong> and occasionally passengers.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tại Scotland, các tàu hơi nước chủ yếu vận chuyển hàng hóa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">cargo</strong>), còn hành khách chỉ là thỉnh thoảng (occasionally).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('63e00ca8-12c6-43e6-972d-b8e86c8c58d6', 'f7dc7a4b-b9f3-42db-8b14-ddf0441a6da6', 'radio', 'Questions 6–13', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information  <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information  <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Pitcher plants increase in size after they have digested a lot of insects."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Carnivorous plants produce light-harvesting enzymes with the nutrients they extract from animals."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Pitcher plants and Venus flytraps are more efficient at photosynthesis than plants with ordinary leaves."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Venus flytraps are better adapted to the soil of swamps and bogs than other carnivorous plants."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Carnivorous plants frequently find it difficult to photosynthesise in bogs due to a lack of sunlight."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Scientists have campaigned to reduce the amount of nitrogen that is released into the soil by agricultural practices."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "A lot of exotic carnivorous plants are sold illegally."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Preventing wildfires is beneficial to the Venus flytrap"}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>6. Pitcher plants increase in size after they have digested a lot of insects.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “When scientists feed <strong>pitcher plants extra bugs, the plants get bigger</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Ăn thêm côn trùng khiến cây nắp ấm tăng kích thước.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>7. Carnivorous plants produce light-harvesting enzymes with the nutrients they extract from animals.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “…take <strong>nitrogen and phosphorus from the flesh in order to build light-harvesting enzymes</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cây ăn thịt sử dụng chất dinh dưỡng từ động vật để tạo enzyme quang hợp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>8. Pitcher plants and Venus flytraps are more efficient at photosynthesis than plants with ordinary leaves.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “A pitcher or a flytrap is <strong>not very good at photosynthesis</strong> because, unlike plants with ordinary leaves…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Chúng kém hiệu quả quang hợp hơn cây có lá thông thường.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>9. Venus flytraps are better adapted to the soil of swamps and bogs than other carnivorous plants.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản chỉ nói chung về khả năng thích nghi của <strong>carnivorous plants</strong> ở bogs, <strong>không so sánh</strong> Venus flytraps với các loài ăn thịt khác.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>10. Carnivorous plants frequently find it difficult to photosynthesise in bogs due to a lack of sunlight.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “Also, bogs are often <strong>flooded with sunshine</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đầm lầy thường ngập tràn ánh nắng, mâu thuẫn với việc thiếu ánh sáng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>11. Scientists have campaigned to reduce the amount of nitrogen that is released into the soil by agricultural practices.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Có thông tin về vấn đề nitơ dư thừa, nhưng <strong>không có thông tin</strong> về việc các nhà khoa học đã tổ chức chiến dịch (campaigned) để giảm nó.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>12. A lot of exotic carnivorous plants are sold illegally.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) “The <strong>black market trade</strong> in exotic carnivorous plants is strong…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> “Black market trade” (thị trường chợ đen) đồng nghĩa với việc buôn bán bất hợp pháp (illegally).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>13. Preventing wildfires is beneficial to the Venus flytrap.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) “The <strong>suppression of wildfires</strong>… <strong>allows other plants to grow quickly and outcompete the Venus flytraps</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Ngăn chặn cháy rừng gây hại vì nó khiến cây khác lấn át cây bắt ruồi Venus.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a55b55a4-240e-4b73-b151-63ba84d0635b', 'fc24b3a2-01e0-4823-8c24-2f07ed60cc63', 'radio', 'Questions 7-13', '', '<p id="p-rc_d9a0518ebc67e1ef-42" data-path-to-node="8,0,0"><span class="citation-2494 citation-2495">Choose</span><strong data-path-to-node="8,0,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-2494 citation-2495"> TRUE</span></strong><span class="citation-2494 citation-2495 citation-end-2495"> if the statement agrees with the information,<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="3"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-2494 citation-end-2494"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="4"><!----></sup></span><strong data-path-to-node="8,1,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-2492 citation-2493">FALSE</span></strong><span class="citation-2492 citation-2493 citation-end-2493"> if the statement contradicts the information,<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="5"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-2492 citation-end-2492"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="6"><!----></sup></span><strong data-path-to-node="8,2,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-2490 citation-2491">NOT GIVEN</span></strong><span class="citation-2490 citation-2491 citation-end-2491"> if there is no information on this</span></p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p> </p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "True"}, {"option_text": "False"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "For steamboats to cross the Atlantic Ocean, engines which used fuel economically were needed."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "True"}, {"option_text": "False"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "Using paddle wheels guaranteed reliability on ocean crossings."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "True"}, {"option_text": "False"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "The Savannah was much faster than a regular paddle steamer."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "True"}, {"option_text": "False"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "Brunel preferred designing railways to steamships."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "True"}, {"option_text": "False"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "The Great Britain had more than one innovative feature."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "True"}, {"option_text": "False"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "The design of the riverboat Archimedes was widely admired."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "True"}, {"option_text": "False"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "Modern ships that cross the Atlantic use the same energy source as the early steamships."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. For steamboats to cross the Atlantic Ocean, engines which used fuel economically were needed. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Travelling under steam power alone would require <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">engines to use less coal</strong> so the ship could stay at sea for several weeks.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để băng qua Đại Tây Dương (open ocean), tàu cần đi liên tục nhiều tuần. Do đó, động cơ phải tiêu thụ ít than hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"126\">use less coal</strong>), tức là sử dụng nhiên liệu một cách tiết kiệm/hiệu quả (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">economically</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. Using paddle wheels guaranteed reliability on ocean crossings. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In order to provide a reliable service, it was also <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">necessary to replace paddle wheels</strong> as a source of power with something <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">less affected by the rolling of the ship</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói rằng để đảm bảo sự tin cậy (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">reliable</strong>), người ta cần <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">thay thế</strong> bánh mái chèo (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">paddle wheels</strong>) vì chúng dễ bị ảnh hưởng bởi sự rung lắc của tàu trên biển. Vậy bánh mái chèo không hề đảm bảo sự tin cậy.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. The Savannah was much faster than a regular paddle steamer. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“crossings under a combination of steam and sail got underway in 1819 with the American ship Savannah.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nhắc đến con tàu Savannah là tàu đầu tiên kết hợp hơi nước và buồm để vượt biển, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">không hề so sánh tốc độ</strong> của nó với các tàu bánh mái chèo thông thường.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. Brunel preferred designing railways to steamships. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Brunel… had already built the Great Western Railway. He created ever bigger ships—faster, more luxurious…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nêu sự thật là Brunel đã xây dựng cả đường sắt và tàu thủy, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">không có thông tin</strong> nào nói ông “thích” (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"126\">preferred</em>) cái nào hơn cái nào.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. The Great Britain had more than one innovative feature. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“His 1853 Great Britain… was the <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">first</strong> ocean-going steamship <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">made of iron</strong>, and the <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">first to use the underwater screw propeller</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Con tàu này có ít nhất hai đặc điểm đổi mới (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">innovative features</strong>) mang tính tiên phong: (1) làm bằng sắt và (2) sử dụng chân vịt thay cho bánh mái chèo.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. The design of the riverboat Archimedes was widely admired. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…only in 1838 did a large steamer use one [the screw], the riverboat Archimedes built by Francis Pettit Smith.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ xác nhận tàu Archimedes là tàu lớn đầu tiên sử dụng chân vịt, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">không đề cập</strong> đến việc thiết kế của nó có được “ngưỡng mộ rộng rãi” (<em data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">widely admired</em>) hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. Modern ships that cross the Atlantic use the same energy source as the early steamships. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In many modern ships, steam turbines have replaced engines with pistons, with <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">fuel oil instead of coal</strong> to fire the boilers. Diesel engines keep others moving.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các tàu hiện đại dùng <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">dầu (fuel oil)</strong> hoặc <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">động cơ Diesel</strong>, trong khi tàu hơi nước đời đầu dùng <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">than (coal)</strong>. Nguồn năng lượng đã thay đổi, không còn giống nhau nữa.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2aa6a478-2afa-4a80-9a81-9443ef87eaa7', 'fa9aeddd-0d39-46d4-ad59-843da2ca1744', 'fillup', 'Question 1-10', '<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<h3><strong>Library services</strong></h3>
<p>Area of living: in the west of Perthon</p>
<p>Best option – Minack Library</p>
<p>Located in {SKELLARN} Street, next to the {park}</p>
<p>Saturdays: open until {4.30|4:30} p.m.</p>
<p><strong>Children’s activities</strong></p>
<p>– a {drama} club (5-13 year olds)</p>
<p>– a {singing} club (every other Saturday)</p>
<p><strong>Adult activities</strong></p>
<p>– book of the Month club</p>
<p>– can meet local {artists} (about one a year)</p>
<p><strong>Services</strong></p>
<p>– can borrow {films}</p>
<p>– computers are available (can be booked)</p>
<p>– various {magazines} are available</p>
<p>– can drop off books, etc via the letter box (must give card {number})</p>
<p><strong>Library shop sells</strong></p>
<p>– postcards (small selection)</p>
<p>– {maps} (wide range)</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a telephone conversation between a man who works for a library service and a woman who wants to join a library. First you have some time to look at questions 1 to 5 on page two. You will see that there is an example that has been done for you. On this occasion only the conversation relating to this will be played first.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Good morning, library services.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> Oh, good morning. My family and I have recently moved to the area and we’d like to find where our nearest library is. We don’t have a car.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Right. So whereabouts are you in Perth?</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> In the west.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Fine. So I’ll just get the details on screen for you.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> The woman is asking about libraries in the west of the area so west has been written in the space. Now we shall begin. You should answer the questions as you listen because you will not hear the recording a second time. Listen carefully and answer questions 1 to five.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Good morning, library services.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> Oh, good morning. My family and I have recently moved to the area and we’d like to find where our nearest library is. We don’t have a car.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Right. So whereabouts are you in Perth?</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> In the west.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Fine. So I’ll just get the details on screen for you. Okay, your nearest one is the Minack Library.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> Minack?</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Yes, in <strong>(1) Skellarn Street</strong>. Can you spell that?</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> It’s S-K-E-L-L-A-R-N Street. Got that.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> It’s very easy to find because it’s next to a <strong>(2) park</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> Oh, I think I know that area. There’s a sports centre near there, isn’t there?</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> I don’t know of one.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> Oh, I’m probably mistaken. Anyway, it’s probably a bit far for us to walk from home. Are there any buses?</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Yes, it’s well served by public transport. There’s a stop about 5 minutes walk away.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> Oh, right. And when does the library open? We’ll most often want to come at the weekend.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> I’m afraid it’s not open on Sunday. Saturday opens at 9:00, closes at <strong>(3) 4:30</strong>. We shut at 5 on weekdays.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> That’s fine. Now I’ve got two kids, 14 and 9, and I wondered whether you have any special activities for them. In our last place, we had an art club.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Well, the library does run a <strong>(4) drama</strong> club, but that would only be suitable for your younger child. It’s open for five to 13 year olds.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> A pity it’s not open to both of them. Have you anything they could both go to?</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Well, there’s no reading club that would suit them both. Oh, but there’s a <strong>(5) singing</strong> club that’s held every second Saturday afternoon for children of all ages up to 16.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> Excellent.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the conversation, you have some time to look at questions 6 to 10 on page two. Now listen and answer questions 6 to ten.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> Now, because we’re new to the area, I’m also wanting to get involved in local activities.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Well, Minack does some sessions for adults as well. There’s a Book of the Month club.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> That’s good.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> And I know that about once every 12 months they have a session where you can meet local <strong>(6) artists</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> How interesting. Well, that sounds like a full program. Now, while I’m on the phone, can I check what the facilities are? Can you take out CDs?</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Not CDs, I’m afraid, but <strong>(7) films</strong>. Yes. Right.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> I’ll make a note of that. Anything else you need to know?</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Oh yes, we have 10 computers and we also stock several <strong>(8) magazines</strong>, including Business, Healthcare, and hobbies. Same as my last place. And there is a new drop off facility where you can post any item through the door if it’s after hours. All you have to do is attach a note to it with the <strong>(9) number</strong> on your card clearly written.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> That sounds good.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> And we do have a small shop on the premises where we sell postcards. We don’t have many, but it’s a popular service. Oh, that’s a good idea. They’re very popular. We also have an impressive range of <strong>(10) maps</strong> of the surrounding area for sale.</p>\n<p><strong>Woman:</strong> Well, it sounds like you’ve got…</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section 1. You now have half a minute to check your answers.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('84b8b664-4c5a-4df8-a3bf-68cd87cbf89c', '4d222311-680e-4f9b-98b0-dc7108da1504', 'matching', 'Questions 27–31', NULL, '<p>Complete the summary using the list of words. Choose the correct answer and move it into the gap.</p>
<div class="p-4"></div>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Characteristics of New Zealand skinks</strong></p>\r\n<p>There are three kinds of reptiles in New Zealand: the tuatara, the gecko and the skink. Skinks are easily distinguished from these other natives by their shiny scale and  {small legs} In common with other reptiles, the grand and Otago species of skink have cold blood and therefore {body heat} must be externally controlled. They are unique in that they do not require a long  {winter sleep} Many species are yet to be identified, and identification depends primarily on their {location} and extremely small physical differences. In {captivity}, skinks may potentially live for about 30 years.</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "eggs"}, {"optionText": "location"}, {"optionText": "hooded eyes"}, {"optionText": "the wild"}, {"optionText": "body heat"}, {"optionText": "winter sleep"}, {"optionText": "captivity"}, {"optionText": "live young"}, {"optionText": "digestive process"}, {"optionText": "small legs"}, {"optionText": "warmer areas"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>27. Skinks are easily distinguished from these other natives by their shiny scale and -&gt; J. small legs</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) “With their gleaming scales, long bodies and often surprisingly <strong>short limbs</strong>, skinks are instantly recognisable.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> “Short limbs” (chi/chân ngắn) đồng nghĩa với <strong>small legs</strong> (chân nhỏ).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>28. In common with other reptiles, the grand and Otago species of skink have cold blood and therefore -&gt; E. body heat</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) “Skinks, being reptiles, need to regulate their temperature, and lie on sunny rocks to absorb <strong>heat</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Là động vật máu lạnh, chúng cần điều chỉnh nhiệt độ/hấp thụ <strong>body heat</strong> (nhiệt độ cơ thể) từ bên ngoài.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>29. They are unique in that they do not require a long -&gt; F. winter sleep</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) “…the grand and Otago are the only kinds that <strong>do not hibernate through winter</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> “Hibernate through winter” (ngủ đông) đồng nghĩa với việc không cần một giấc ngủ đông dài (<strong>winter sleep</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>30. Many species are yet to be identified, and identification depends primarily on their -&gt; B. location</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) “<strong>Identification depends on where specimens are found</strong>, and such minutiae as the number of scales on their toes.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc nhận dạng phụ thuộc vào nơi tìm thấy (location).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>31. In -&gt; G. captivity, skinks may potentially live for about 30 years.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) “…although in <strong>zoos or research centres</strong> they can live beyond thirty.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Vườn thú và trung tâm nghiên cứu là các hình thức <strong>nuôi nhốt</strong> (<strong>captivity</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('72f18f93-977d-488c-bcfb-0f8110721d07', 'a1784c9b-5e46-47c1-86c3-1c5b1306d7a6', 'matching', 'Questions 14-19', '', '<p>Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="117">A-F</strong>, in boxes 14-19 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_headings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. Interpreting the research behind who is participating in art activities"}, {"optionText": "ii. How sales of artwork have increased in many countries"}, {"optionText": "iii. Two opportunities for getting kids involved in art activities"}, {"optionText": "iv. How art can be made accessible to the public"}, {"optionText": "v. Developing a model to explain the lack of participation in art"}, {"optionText": "vi. The connection between art and media"}, {"optionText": "vii. How involvement with art affects well-being and attitudes"}, {"optionText": "viii. How art makes communities safer and more vital"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Section A — {vii. How involvement with art affects well-being and attitudes}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Self-expression… promotes <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">individuality</strong>, bolsters <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">self-confidence</strong> and improves <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">motivation and attitudes</strong> towards academic performance… provide the benefits of discovery, stimulation and <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"201\">relaxation</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn A tập trung vào tác động của nghệ thuật đối với cá nhân: giúp tự tin hơn, cải thiện thái độ học tập và mang lại sự thư giãn (tất cả đều thuộc về sức khỏe tinh thần – wellbeing và thái độ – attitudes).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Section B — {viii. How art makes communities safer and more vital}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Art programs can be highly effective in <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">reducing community problems</strong> related to delinquent behavior… creating a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">positive, productive and creative outlet</strong>… instilling a sense of pride… and civic responsibility.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn B nói về việc nghệ thuật giúp giảm bớt các tệ nạn (delinquent behavior) ở thanh thiếu niên và làm cho cộng đồng đáng sống hơn (livable), thu hút kinh doanh và du lịch (vitality).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Section C — {iv. How art can be made accessible to the public}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Public art programs are one way. These programs are typically administered by government… for <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">display in public spaces</strong>. Public art works can include <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"163\">street furniture, decorations, paving and landmarks</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Accessible” có nghĩa là dễ dàng tiếp cận. Đoạn C mô tả cách đưa nghệ thuật vào không gian công cộng (đường phố, vỉa hè) để mọi người đều có thể trải nghiệm trong cuộc sống hàng ngày.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Section D — {v. Developing a model to explain the lack of participation in art}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If art experiences are so beneficial, <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">why aren’t more people participating?</strong>… the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">RAND Corporation</strong>… developed <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">‘A Behavior Model of the Participant Decision’</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sau khi nêu ra các số liệu về việc ít người tham gia nghệ thuật (lack of participation), đoạn D giới thiệu về một mô hình (model) của tổ chức RAND để giải thích hành vi và quyết định của người tham gia.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Section E — {i. Interpreting the research behind who is participating in art activities}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The RAND findings reveal that the <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">disinclined</strong> perceive themselves as being uncomfortable… The <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">inclined</strong> are interested… <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">Current participants</strong> are those who are involved…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn E đi sâu vào phân tích (interpret) các nhóm đối tượng cụ thể dựa trên kết quả nghiên cứu của RAND: nhóm không hứng thú, nhóm có hứng thú nhưng bị rào cản, và nhóm đang tham gia.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Section F — {iii. Two opportunities for getting kids involved in art activities}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…offer <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">two innovative programs</strong>: The <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">National Photography Program</strong> and the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">National Fine Arts Exhibit</strong>. Both are designed to get <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">children excited about art</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn F giới thiệu cụ thể 2 chương trình (two opportunities) của tổ chức Boys and Girls Clubs nhằm giúp trẻ em tiếp cận và hào hứng với nghệ thuật.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fff6b7d7-c935-416d-8c5e-acc3ed611857', 'a1784c9b-5e46-47c1-86c3-1c5b1306d7a6', 'matrix', 'Questions 20-23', '', '<p>Match each statement with the correct researcher, <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="136">A-F</strong>.</p>
<p>Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="167">A-F</strong>, in boxes 20-23 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Art activities can contribute to lowering negative incidents associated with juvenile crime.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Art can bring money and visitors into a community.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Commercial interests are drawn to areas that emphasise public art.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Art activities can both energise and calm people.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Spector", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Oliphant", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Riley", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Hughes", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('dce42f42-309f-4740-83bf-318f0266c491', 'a1784c9b-5e46-47c1-86c3-1c5b1306d7a6', 'fillup', 'Questions 24-26', '<p>Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong data-path-to-node="9" data-index-in-node="37">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 24-26 on your answer sheet.</p>
<ul data-path-to-node="10">
<li>
<p>Sometimes people want to get involved in art activities but can’t afford it, can’t fit it into their schedule, or don’t have the suitable {attire}.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>A noticeable correlation exists between art involvement in childhood and those in {adulthood}.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The National Photography Program allows members to grow personally and also gain {recognition} for their artistic achievements.</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. Sometimes people want to get involved in art activities but can’t afford it, can’t fit it into their schedule, or don’t have the suitable {attire}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The inclined are interested in participating, but may be constrained by particular barriers, such as <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">cost</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">time</strong>, and proper <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"145\">attire</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi sử dụng cách diễn đạt khác (paraphrasing) cho các rào cản:\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1\">\n<li><em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Can’t afford it</em> (không đủ khả năng chi trả) = <em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">Cost</em>.</li>\n<li><em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Can’t fit it into their schedule</em> (không sắp xếp được thời gian) = <em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">Time</em>.</li>\n<li><em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Don’t have the suitable attire</em> (không có trang phục phù hợp) = <em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">Proper <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">attire</strong></em>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. A noticeable correlation exists between art involvement in childhood and those in {adulthood}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Researchers suggest that a strong relationship exists between <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">childhood</strong> and <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">adult</strong> art participation rates. Individuals with a greater number of childhood art experiences are more likely to have higher rates of participation as <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"248\">adults</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Noticeable correlation” tương ứng với “strong relationship”. Bài đọc chỉ ra mối liên hệ giữa việc tham gia nghệ thuật khi còn nhỏ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">childhood</strong>) và khi đã trưởng thành (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"179\">adulthood/adults</strong>). Từ cần điền ở đây phải là danh từ “adulthood” để tương ứng về mặt ngữ pháp với “childhood”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. The National Photography Program allows members to grow personally and also gain {recognition} for their artistic achievements.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The program provides club members with the opportunity to achieve <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">personal growth</strong> and receive <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">artistic recognition</strong> through instruction in photography.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “grow personally” tương ứng với “personal growth”. “Gain” tương ứng với “receive”. Thành quả thứ hai mà các thành viên nhận được chính là sự công nhận về mặt nghệ thuật (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"186\">artistic recognition</strong>). Vì đề yêu cầu 1 từ, chúng ta chọn danh từ chính là <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"260\">recognition</strong>.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8061bfbf-73da-46a3-a1ba-b7d86eb5f928', '653a6ba7-22f8-4906-a973-2d745ffada7a', 'fillup', 'Questions 11-15', '<p>Complete the sentences below</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer</p>
<p>Special conditions may apply to {overseas} students looking for a<br />
job.</p>
<p>The university Job Centre is located on the {Woodside} Campus.</p>
<p>The Job Centre remains open until {8pm} every evening.</p>
<p>The only day the employment lawyer is available is {Tuesday}</p>
<p>The university {website} regularly advertises new jobs</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>SECTION 2</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Marissa:</strong> Hi, thanks for coming along. My name is Marissa and I’m going to tell you a bit about finding part-time jobs. Not everybody wants to work when they’re studying, and as this is your first year, you may feel that you’ve quite enough to do as it is. But you may change your mind or find that you need to earn some extra cash.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">However, if you are a student from <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><u>(11) overseas</u></strong><u>,</u></span> there may be particular conditions attached to working in this country, so you should check with the staff at the centre before applying for a job.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Right now, the university has its own Job Centre on the campus. Well, actually it’s not on this main Hilston campus; it’s based in the Student Services building on the campus called <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><u>(12) Woodside</u></strong> (spelt W-O-O-D-S-I-D-E). </span>The centre works on a drop-in basis, which means that you don’t have to make an appointment. It’s open six days a week, Monday to Saturday, and nine hours a day, from 10 in the morning until <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><u>(13) 8 at night (8pm)</u></strong></span><u>.</u></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The centre is run by other students, but a professional employment lawyer is on hand every<u> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(14) Tuesday</strong></span></u> if you want any advice about your job. There may be a queue, in which case you will have to wait, so make sure you allow plenty of time. Part-time jobs become available almost every day, and they are advertised on the university <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><u>(15) website</u></strong>, </span>which you can access through the library if the computer centre is closed. You should check things daily, and if you see a job which interests you, call in at the centre.</p>\n<div class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\">\n<hr align=\"center\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Marissa:</strong> There’s a good variety of jobs on offer in the university itself just now. For example, they’re looking for people to check that all the vehicles using the university <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><u>(16) car parks</u></strong><u> have got up-to-date permits <strong>(C)</strong></u>. </span>Office jobs rarely come up, but in future, the university is hoping to be able to offer jobs in the IT centre.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">There are also recruitment open days which are held <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><u>(17) regularly during the year (C: throughout the year)</u></strong><u>,</u></span> when local employers come into the university to recruit students for part-time work within their company. These two-day events are scheduled well in advance each term and are advertised in the usual places.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Of course, part-time work is useful to supplement your income, but it’s also a valuable way of <strong><u><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\">(18) building up an employment record that reflects your skills and capabilities (B: provide a useful work record for the</span> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\">future)</span></u></strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><u>. </u></span>One of the most common complaints of graduates leaving university is that many jobs require proven experience, so those applicants who have evidence of part-time work on their CV often have an advantage.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Job Centre advertises jobs which will give you skills such as using word processing packages, spreadsheets or supervisory skills. So if you have to work, use the opportunity to develop skills which will help you secure a job in the future.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now, what about the financial side of things? Well, students who work part-time can no longer expect to be paid cash.<span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"> <strong><u>(19) An employer will deduct tax from what you earn (A: will be taxed)</u></strong></span><u><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\">,</span> </u>but depending on your own individual circumstances and how much you earn in a year, you should be able to reclaim some of this. You may also have to contribute towards an insurance scheme, but you must ask your employer about these deductions.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">You should also check whether you will be paid weekly or monthly and if you work extra hours, what your overtime rate will be. It’s also necessary to make sure that your employer knows that you may only be able to work during term time. Communication between you and your employer is very important, but don’t expect all employers to use email. If you are ill or cannot get into work for whatever reason, make sure your employer knows in good time—that shouldn’t be a problem now that everyone has a mobile phone. And if you decide to leave the job, you should make sure you<u><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"> <strong>(20) put this in writing (A: give notice in writing)</strong>.</span> </u>Some employers require a month’s notice, even for a part-time job.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">So what sort of work can you expect to find? Well, as I said earlier…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cf6970fb-5d97-4978-9f10-530041000fbd', '4d222311-680e-4f9b-98b0-dc7108da1504', 'radio', 'Questions 32–36', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the views of the writer. <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts what the writer thinks. <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if it is impossible to know what the writer’s point of view is.</p>
<div class="space-y-1">
<div class="space-y-2"></div>
</div>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The DOC project to remove feral cats helped stop the decline in Otago skink numbers."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Parasite infections are having a serious effect on the physical condition of wild skinks"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The best possible habitat for the conservation of skinks is unknown"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It is possible that skinks used to have larger numbers of young than they do now"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The survival of the common species of skink may soon be at risk"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>32. The DOC project to remove feral cats helped stop the decline in Otago skink numbers.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: NO</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “<strong>Despite the capture of hundreds of cats, skinks showed no signs of recovery; indeed, there were further declines.</strong>“</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Dự án không những không giúp đỡ mà số lượng skink còn tiếp tục giảm, mâu thuẫn với câu hỏi.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>33. Parasite infections are having a serious effect on the physical condition of wild skinks.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: NO</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “<strong>Although no direct health implications have been detected</strong> the trend is a concern…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Hiện tại, <strong>chưa phát hiện</strong> ra ảnh hưởng trực tiếp nghiêm trọng nào đến sức khỏe của skink hoang dã.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>34. The best possible habitat for the conservation of skinks is unknown.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: YES</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “<strong>Even if we had the answer to the eradication of predators, we haven’t a clue to the habitat we should be recreating for the skinks</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định họ không biết môi trường sống nào là tốt nhất cho việc bảo tồn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>35. It is possible that skinks used to have larger numbers of young than they do now.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> Văn bản chỉ so sánh khả năng sinh sản <strong>giữa các loài skink hiện tại</strong> (grand/Otago sinh ít hơn loài phổ biến) nhưng <strong>không so sánh</strong> số lượng con non của cùng một loài qua các thời kỳ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>36. The survival of the common species of skink may soon be at risk.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: YES</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “<strong>As more is learned about the size of skink populations, it becomes clear that even common species may be facing a doubtful future</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả cho rằng ngay cả các loài phổ biến cũng đang đối mặt với nguy cơ trong tương lai.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('dab493a2-eaec-4f47-81d4-397cd2cefbf0', '63ec898c-bed9-4489-bb40-eef5c5529c79', 'matrix', 'Questions 32–40', NULL, '<p>Classify the following statements as referring to</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of options", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "The student composition of each class was left to chance", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "A long-term improvement in performance was claimed.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Similar results were obtained for all social groups", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "The project was a preliminary to a more comprehensive study.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Several different class types were involved in the project.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "A special group of schools was selected to take part.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Classroom assistants were used as part of the project.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "The project was responsible for aggravating existing problems", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Certain groups of pupils within the sample were identified as having benefited", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Project STAR", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "The California Project", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "SAGE", "categoryLetter": "C"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>32. The student composition of each class was left to chance.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: A</strong> (Project STAR)</li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “Students entering kindergarten were <strong>randomly assigned</strong> to one of three kinds of classes…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Học sinh được phân công ngẫu nhiên (randomly assigned) vào các loại lớp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>33. A long-term improvement in performance was claimed.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: A</strong> (Project STAR)</li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “…this advantage <strong>persisted even after students returned to larger classes</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Lợi thế học tập vẫn duy trì ngay cả khi học sinh chuyển về lớp lớn hơn (long-term improvement).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>34. Similar results were obtained for all social groups.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: B</strong> (The California Project)</li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “Researchers found a statistically significant achievement advantage… What is more, <strong>the effect did not vary for students of different backgrounds</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Kết quả không khác biệt giữa các học sinh có hoàn cảnh khác nhau.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>35. The project was a preliminary to a more comprehensive study.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: C</strong> (SAGE)</li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “Wisconsin’s SAGE was a five-year <strong>pilot study to do some of the groundwork for a major project</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> SAGE là một nghiên cứu thử nghiệm (pilot study) chuẩn bị cho một dự án lớn hơn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>36. Several different class types were involved in the project.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: A</strong> (Project STAR)</li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “…randomly assigned to <strong>one of three kinds of classes</strong>: a small class… a regular-size class… or a regular-size class with both a teacher and a full-time teacher’s aide.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>37. A special group of schools was selected to take part.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: C</strong> (SAGE)</li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “…it was noteworthy for <strong>targeting schools at which 30% of the students were below poverty level</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> SAGE chọn các trường có tỷ lệ học sinh nghèo cao.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>38. Classroom assistants were used as part of the project.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: A</strong> (Project STAR)</li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “…a regular-size class with both a teacher and a <strong>full-time teacher’s aide</strong>.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>39. The project was responsible for aggravating existing problems.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: B</strong> (The California Project)</li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “This is <strong>exacerbating the disparity</strong> in resources available to rich and poor schools in California…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Dự án California làm trầm trọng thêm (aggravating) sự chênh lệch (disparity) giữa trường giàu và trường nghèo.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>40. Certain groups of pupils within the sample were identified as having benefited.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: A</strong> (Project STAR)</li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “They also found that the effect was <strong>stronger for black and Hispanic minority groups</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các nhóm thiểu số (black and Hispanic) được xác định là hưởng lợi nhiều hơn.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2b00954b-0799-48fa-821b-24a52c4642f8', '4d222311-680e-4f9b-98b0-dc7108da1504', 'radio', 'Questions 37–40', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A More data is necessary in order for DOC to target the right areas. "}, {"content": "B DOC is uncertain how long a new strategy will take to be effective."}, {"content": "C There is a considerable risk that DOC will not succeed in saving them. "}, {"content": "D The first step in DOC''s strategy is to identify their main predator."}], "question": "According to the sixth paragraph, what is being said about the future of the grand and Otago skinks?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A the fence needed to surround various kinds of habitat."}, {"content": "B the fence was not the preferred choice of some conservationists. "}, {"content": "C the fence had to be constructed near a heavily populated urban area."}, {"content": "D there was no way of knowing how many skinks were inside the fence."}], "question": "According to the writer, a problem with the DOC''s fencing project was that"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A introduce a recent alternative approach to skink conservation. "}, {"content": "B question whether captive breeding has worked in the past."}, {"content": "C imply that skinks are unlikely to reproduce outside their usual habitat. "}, {"content": "D express a preference for conserving skinks in their natural environment."}], "question": "The writer uses the phrase ''a last resort'' in the eighth paragraph in order to"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A referring to obstacles in the way of skink conservation "}, {"content": "B appealing to landowners to donate land for conservation purposes"}, {"content": "C describing a conservation scheme that is being set up on farmland"}, {"content": "D showing how commercial profit can be made from ecological ventures"}], "question": "What is the writer doing in the final paragraph?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>37. According to the sixth paragraph, what is being said about the future of the grand and Otago skinks?</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: C. There is a considerable risk that DOC will not succeed in saving them.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “<strong>No more than five years remain in which to turn things around</strong> – a close call considering it will be at least three before detectable response in the populations can be expected…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Với thời gian còn lại rất ít (5 năm) và tốc độ sinh sản chậm, có một <strong>nguy cơ lớn</strong> (considerable risk) là DOC sẽ thất bại trong việc cứu chúng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>38. According to the writer, a problem with the DOC’s fencing project was that</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: A. the fence needed to surround various kinds of habitat.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “An added complication was that <strong>grands and Otagos have subtly different environmental preferences, both of which need catering for</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc hai loài có sở thích môi trường khác nhau đòi hỏi hàng rào phải bao quanh nhiều loại môi trường sống (various kinds of habitat) để đáp ứng cả hai.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>39. The writer uses the phrase ‘a last resort’ in the eighth paragraph in order to</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: D. express a preference for conserving skinks in their natural environment.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn H) “Captive management, however, is <strong>a last resort</strong>. The <strong>priority is to manage and protect skinks in the wild</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Gọi nuôi nhốt là “phương sách cuối cùng” (“a last resort”) và nhấn mạnh <strong>ưu tiên</strong> là bảo vệ trong tự nhiên cho thấy tác giả ủng hộ việc bảo tồn trong môi trường tự nhiên.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>40. What is the writer doing in the final paragraph?</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: C. describing a conservation scheme that is being set up on farmland.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn J) “…with the generous support of a local <strong>farmer with grazing land</strong> there, has begun the construction of a mammal-proof fence…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn mô tả chương trình hợp tác với nông dân để xây dựng hàng rào bảo vệ trên đất chăn thả (<strong>farmland</strong>) của họ.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f8eed65b-ba89-42e0-86f4-82c506b8ab7e', '653a6ba7-22f8-4906-a973-2d745ffada7a', 'radio', 'Questions 16-20', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answers</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "its offices"}, {"content": "the IT centre"}, {"content": "the car parks"}], "question": "At present, the university is offering part-time work in"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "only in the first term"}, {"content": "twice a term"}, {"content": "throughout the year"}], "question": "Local employers visit the university"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "lead to a full-time job after graduation"}, {"content": "provide a useful work record for the future"}, {"content": "give the chance to develop team-work skills"}], "question": "According to the speaker, a part-time job can"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "will be taxed"}, {"content": "will be paid every week"}, {"content": "will need private insurance"}], "question": "Students who work part-time"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "give notice in writing"}, {"content": "communicate by email"}, {"content": "have a mobile phone"}], "question": "Part-time student workers are advised to"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('36a58afc-6613-4cef-aa2b-8a6983c4852f', 'ecde7963-d53b-489b-87ef-32006e045dc8', 'fillup', 'Questions 14–16', '<p data-start="20" data-end="181">Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p data-start="20" data-end="181">Choose <strong data-start="63" data-end="89">NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="183" data-end="266">The black-footed ferret shares most characteristics with the {Siberian polecat}.</p>
<p data-start="268" data-end="354">North American ferrets are thought to have originally come from {Europe}.</p>
<p data-start="356" data-end="434">The {prairie dog} is the black-footed ferret''s primary source of food.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Siberian polecat — {The black-footed ferret shares most characteristics with the Siberian polecat.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">Siberian polecat looks more similar to the black-footed ferret, and leads a similar life</strong> on open grasslands and semi-desert regions...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói về loài vật mà chồn chân đen chia sẻ nhiều đặc tính nhất (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">shares most characteristics with</em>). Bài đọc viết rằng loài chồn sương Siberia (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">Siberian polecat</strong>) trông giống với chồn chân đen hơn (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"213\">looks more similar</em>) và có lối sống tương đồng (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"260\">leads a similar life</em>). Từ cần điền là <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"298\">Siberian polecat</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Europe — {North American ferrets are thought to have originally come from Europe.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">Ferrets probably evolved in Europe</strong> between three and four million years ago, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">and dispersed into North America</strong> across an ice-age land bridge...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Originally come from\" (đến từ đâu một cách nguyên bản/nguồn gốc) đồng nghĩa với động từ tiến hóa, hình thành ban đầu (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">evolved in</em>). Loài chồn này tiến hóa ở Châu Âu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"178\">Europe</strong>) trước khi di cư, phân tán vào Bắc Mỹ (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"224\">dispersed into North America</em>). Từ cần điền là <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"270\">Europe</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. prairie dog — {The prairie dog is the black-footed ferret''s primary source of food.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The black-footed ferret''s history in North America is <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">inextricably linked to the creature which became almost its sole prey - the prairie dog</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Primary source of food\" (nguồn thức ăn chính yếu) đồng nghĩa hoàn toàn với cụm từ \"almost its sole prey\" (gần như là con mồi duy nhất). Con mồi/Nguồn thức ăn duy nhất này của chồn chân đen chính là loài chó đồng cỏ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"229\">prairie dog</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d8aaddec-a748-4634-9e9c-342b60aecfe2', '1f388ca3-a8a3-4e15-86cf-d0f35f570a4f', 'radio', 'Questions 27-30', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="27">A, B, C</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="38">D</strong>.</p>
<p>Write the correct letter in boxes 27-30 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A. had been programmed to predict his moves."}, {"option_text": "B. was able to see into his own thought processes."}, {"option_text": "C. used powers that were potentially dangerous to humans."}, {"option_text": "D. was fundamentally different from others he had encountered."}], "question": "When playing chess against the computer Deep Blue, Kasparov felt that it"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. In the last 50 years machines have advanced more quickly than expected."}, {"option_text": "B. There are certain features of chess that machines cannot replicate."}, {"option_text": "C. Skill at chess is more significant than other machine achievements."}, {"option_text": "D. Machines will always be more successful at some tasks than at others."}], "question": "What is the writer’s main idea in the third paragraph?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. everyday human actions involve a complex combination of skills."}, {"option_text": "B. some types of mechanical activities require little conscious thought."}, {"option_text": "C. some people are able to carry out multiple tasks at the same time."}, {"option_text": "D. certain human tasks are more intellectually demanding than others."}], "question": "The writer describes the case of an office worker to illustrate the point that"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. ideas of what success means vary across cultures."}, {"option_text": "B. machines are most effective at game-like activities."}, {"option_text": "C. machines are better at specialisation than at adaptation."}, {"option_text": "D. it may be impossible to isolate different skills involved in an activity."}], "question": "In the fifth paragraph, the writer claims that"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. When playing chess against the computer Deep Blue, Kasparov felt that it — {D. was fundamentally different from others he had encountered.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Kasparov had beaten <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">previous</strong> computer chess programs, which to him seemed <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">predictable and mechanical</strong>, but he allegedly said he sensed an <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">‘alien intelligence’</strong> on the other side of the board when he played against <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"233\">Deep Blue</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Kasparov nhận thấy Deep Blue khác hẳn những chương trình trước đây (vốn máy móc và dễ đoán). Ông cảm nhận được một “trí tuệ ngoài hành tinh” (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"154\">alien intelligence</strong>), điều này cho thấy Deep Blue cơ bản là khác biệt (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"224\">fundamentally different</strong>) so với những gì ông từng gặp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. What is the writer’s main idea in the third paragraph? — {C. Skill at chess is more significant than other machine achievements.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“But <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">intellectual prowess</strong> is what sets human beings apart… and <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">chess is a supremely intellectual pursuit</strong>.”</em> Tác giả cũng so sánh với việc xe chạy nhanh hơn người hay cần cẩu nâng nặng hơn, nhưng cho rằng việc thắng ở môn cờ vua mới là đỉnh cao vì nó đánh vào trí tuệ.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả nhấn mạnh rằng mặc dù máy móc đã vượt qua con người ở nhiều mặt vật lý (tốc độ, sức mạnh), nhưng kỹ năng chơi cờ vua có ý nghĩa quan trọng hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">more significant</strong>) vì nó đại diện cho trí thông minh thuần túy của con người.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. The writer describes the case of an office worker to illustrate the point that — {A. everyday human actions involve a complex combination of skills.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Her day has no doubt been a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">busy patchwork of activities</strong>… Each of these activities requires the exercise of <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">multiple sensorimotor skills</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ví dụ về người nhân viên văn phòng (làm đồ ăn trưa, lái xe, sửa máy photo…) được đưa ra để chứng minh rằng một người bình thường thực hiện các hành động hàng ngày dựa trên sự kết hợp phức tạp của nhiều kỹ năng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"225\">complex combination of skills</strong>), khác với máy móc chỉ làm được một việc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. In the fifth paragraph, the writer claims that — {C. machines are better at specialisation than at adaptation.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The achievements of AI research in a variety of <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">specialist domains</strong>… contrast starkly with the field’s failure to produce a machine with <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"159\">general purpose, adaptive intelligence</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định AI đã thành công rực rỡ trong các lĩnh vực chuyên biệt (specialist domains) nhưng lại thất bại trong việc tạo ra một cỗ máy có khả năng thích nghi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"179\">adaptive</strong>) và đa năng như con người.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('55bc84b3-ad08-4056-88a7-8ebd94c78f36', '1f388ca3-a8a3-4e15-86cf-d0f35f570a4f', 'fillup', 'Questions 31-36', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="35">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 31-36 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="0">Embodiment: an essential feature</strong></span></p>
<p>Unlike machines, animals (including humans) have a body, including a brain which has evolved to provide {protection} for that body and allow its genes to be passed on. An animal’s senses provide it with information about its {environment} and then through {muscles} it can react physically to what it senses. The interaction of the body and brain therefore allows the creation of a link between {perception} and action. The {capacities} which make us human and which distinguish us from animals have their {foundation} in this link between the brain and the body, and have developed from it.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. Unlike machines, animals (including humans) have a body, including a brain which has evolved to provide {protection} for that body…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The brain of an animal has evolved to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">prevent any harm from coming to that body</strong> and to perpetuate the genes that it carries.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “prevent any harm from coming to that body” (ngăn chặn bất kỳ tổn hại nào đến cơ thể) chính là chức năng bảo vệ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">protection</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. An animal’s senses provide it with information about its {environment}…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The body has muscles, enabling it to move, and senses, so that its actions can be made to react to the state of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"137\">environment</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các giác quan giúp sinh vật nhận biết và phản ứng lại trạng thái của môi trường xung quanh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">environment</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. …and then through {muscles} it can react physically to what it senses.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The body has <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">muscles</strong>, enabling it to move…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Chính nhờ các cơ bắp (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">muscles</strong>) mà cơ thể có thể thực hiện các chuyển động vật lý để phản ứng lại những gì nó cảm nhận được.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. The interaction of the body and brain therefore allows the creation of a link between {perception} and action.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The brain shapes the animal’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">actions</strong> according to what it <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">perceives</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ “perceives” (động từ) trong bài được chuyển thành danh từ <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">perception</strong> (sự nhận thức) trong câu tóm tắt để chỉ mối liên kết giữa nhận thức và hành động.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. The {capacities} which make us human and which distinguish us from animals…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…and the human <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">capacities</strong> for language, reason, and creativity all rest on a sensorimotor foundation.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc dùng từ “capacities” (năng lực) để chỉ những đặc điểm riêng biệt của con người như ngôn ngữ, lý trí và sáng tạo.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. …have their {foundation} in this link between the brain and the body, and have developed from it.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…all rest on a sensorimotor <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">foundation</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mọi năng lực cao cấp của con người đều dựa trên nền tảng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">foundation</strong>) là hệ thống cảm giác – vận động (mối liên kết cơ thể – trí não).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5b9b5116-be09-47aa-9eb8-58354e55da5d', 'e455450a-760d-44a6-a406-72b5bda8c75f', 'fillup', 'Questions 11–16', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the table below</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<table class="MsoNormalTable" style="width: 76.18%; border-collapse: collapse; border: none; height: 327.569px;" border="1" width="76%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 70.3993px;">
<td style="border: 1.5pt inset black; padding: 0.75pt; width: 24.2849%; text-align: center;"><strong>Vacation job</strong></td>
<td style="border-top: 1.5pt inset black; border-right: 1.5pt inset black; border-bottom: 1.5pt inset black; border-image: initial; border-left: none; padding: 0.75pt; width: 23.164%; text-align: center;"><strong>Main advantage</strong></td>
<td style="border-top: 1.5pt inset black; border-right: 1.5pt inset black; border-bottom: 1.5pt inset black; border-image: initial; border-left: none; padding: 0.75pt; width: 26.7134%; text-align: center;"><strong>Main disadvantage</strong></td>
<td style="border-top: 1.5pt inset black; border-right: 1.5pt inset black; border-bottom: 1.5pt inset black; border-image: initial; border-left: none; padding: 0.75pt; width: 25.7793%; text-align: center;"><strong>Recommendation</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 88.3854px;">
<td style="border-right: 1.5pt inset black; border-bottom: 1.5pt inset black; border-left: 1.5pt inset black; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0.75pt; width: 24.2849%;"> Stocktaking</td>
<td style="border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1.5pt inset black; border-right: 1.5pt inset black; padding: 0.75pt; width: 23.164%;">{travelling | traveling}</td>
<td style="border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1.5pt inset black; border-right: 1.5pt inset black; padding: 0.75pt; width: 26.7134%;"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"> <span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: #000000;">tiring</span></span></td>
<td style="border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1.5pt inset black; border-right: 1.5pt inset black; padding: 0.75pt; width: 25.7793%;">{get good shoes}</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 84.3924px;">
<td style="border: 1.5pt inset black; padding: 0.75pt; width: 24.2849%;">
<p class="MsoNormal">Office work</p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1.5pt inset black; padding: 0.75pt; width: 23.164%;">
<p class="MsoNormal">air conditioning</p>
</td>
<td style="border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1.5pt inset black; border-right: 1.5pt inset black; padding: 0.75pt; width: 26.7134%;">{wearing formal clothes}</td>
<td style="border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1.5pt inset black; border-right: 1.5pt inset black; padding: 0.75pt; width: 25.7793%;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Calibri'',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">choose a </span>{large office}</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 84.3924px;">
<td style="border: 1.5pt inset black; padding: 0.75pt; width: 24.2849%;">
<p class="MsoNormal">Theme park attendant</p>
</td>
<td style="border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1.5pt inset black; border-right: 1.5pt inset black; padding: 0.75pt; width: 23.164%;">{good pay}</td>
<td style="border: 1.5pt inset black; padding: 0.75pt; width: 26.7134%;">
<p class="MsoNormal">rude customers</p>
</td>
