', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 2</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sarah:</strong> Welcome to Student Life. <span class=\"citation-633 citation-end-633\">It’s spring, and many of you may be thinking about arranging work for the long vacation. So, on today’s program, Roger Anwell reports on a survey we conducted into the pleasures and problems of vacation jobs. Roger.</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Roger:</strong> Thank you, Sarah. <span class=\"citation-632 citation-end-632\">Well, the first thing to say is that by far the majority of students we surveyed did just three types of jobs. All of these obviously had their advantages and disadvantages.</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><span class=\"citation-631 citation-end-631\">Starting with stocktaking in supermarkets. The thing that students said they enjoyed most about this job wa</span>s the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">(11) travelling</strong>. They were often required to go to branches to do their stocktakes, <span class=\"citation-629 citation-630 citation-end-630\">and this was regarded as an interesting plus. The main negative, however, was that they tended to find the job tiring, with long hours spent on their feet and climbing high shelves. Now, one thing we did ask the students in our survey was whether</span><span class=\"citation-629 citation-end-629\"> they had any recommendations for other people taking on their job, and they said, perhaps not surprisin</span>gly, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"552\">(12) <span class=\"citation-628\">get good shoes</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-628 citation-end-628\">. That’s the only way you can keep going.</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><span class=\"citation-627 citation-end-627\">Another job which lots of students did was office work, and the positive feature of this actually rather surprised me, until I remembered what a hot summer it was last year. Lots of students named air conditioning as the best thing about office work. The downside which many talked about wa</span>s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"292\">(13) wearing formal clothes</strong></span>. Obviously, this didn’t go down too well with students. The advice most people gave was to select a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"420\">(14) large office</strong></span>. That way you have more variety of social contacts, otherwise the work can get very boring.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">The third job which had attracted large numbers of students was as a theme park attendant. And again, I got a surprise here, because the big plus people talked about was <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">(15) good pay</strong></span>. It must have improved since my day, I must say! Anyway, the downside I did recognize—having to deal with difficult customers, especially in the heat when tempers get frayed. Not easy. And people said that it was a good idea to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"412\">(16) live nearby</strong></span> ’cause there’s a lot of shift work and you don’t have to worry about transport at difficult times of the day.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"8\" />\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Roger:</strong> <span class=\"citation-625 citation-626 citation-end-626\">So those were the findings from the survey on the most common student jobs. But not all student jobs have to be mundane and boring. One of the students who responded in our survey spoke at length about his ama</span><span class=\"citation-625 citation-end-625\">zing job as a zoo attendant.</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><span class=\"citation-624\">Peter Marshall had read about work opportunities </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"49\"><span class=\"citation-624 citation-end-624\">(</span>17) on the zoo website (B)</strong> </span><span class=\"citation-623 citation-end-623\">and just went along with a friend to talk to someone in personnel. He was offered a job there and then—as easy as that! In previous years, he’d done singularly unexciting shop work, so he was very pleased to be doing such</span> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"299\">(18) original work (C: unusual)</strong></span>.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><span class=\"citation-621 citation-622 citation-end-622\">He ended up working for just under three months, which was actually slightly more than he had anticipated and meant that he had to miss part of university term time, but he said it was well worth it because he thinks he’s found his future career path as a result of this experience. He loved working on the educational side in part</span><span class=\"citation-621\">icular, </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"339\"><span class=\"citation-621 citation-end-621\">(</span>19) helping young kids understand about the animals (B)</strong></span></span> in their natural environment. He said it was the most intriguing thing he’d ever done.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">He tells us, though, that with final exams coming up, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">(20) he won’t be able to do any paid work (A)</strong></span> this coming vacation. So why don’t you apply? If you’re interested in getting further information about the findings of the survey…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('53aa6350-289e-4482-949d-d544d583464e', 'e455450a-760d-44a6-a406-72b5bda8c75f', 'radio', 'Questions 17–20', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "from a collenge friend."}, {"content": "on the computer."}, {"content": "from a student job centre."}], "question": "Peter learned about the job"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "easy."}, {"content": "challenging."}, {"content": "unusual."}], "question": "Peter mainly enjoyed the job because it was"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "learning about the environment."}, {"content": "working with children."}, {"content": "caring for the animals."}], "question": "The job’s most interesting aspect was"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "won’t take a job."}, {"content": "will work at the zoo."}, {"content": "will work elsewhere."}], "question": "Peter has decided that next vacation he"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('380e91fd-a579-4ffe-b80d-8a10d7596747', 'fdfbb0e0-1209-4ede-a0f2-73bf7cb50bb1', 'matching', 'Questions 27–33', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below.</p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i Moving rapidly across the desert"}, {"optionText": "ii Recreating the process in a laboratory"}, {"optionText": "iii Strange music created by human movement"}, {"optionText": "iv A potential threat to industry and communications"}, {"optionText": "v Dunes coming together and re-forming"}, {"optionText": "vi Needing a specific combination of conditions"}, {"optionText": "vii A continuous cycle"}, {"optionText": "viii The commonest type of dune"}, {"optionText": "ix Old superstitions demystified"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>27. Paragraph A</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: iv. A potential threat to industry and communications</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn A mô tả các đụn cát khổng lồ đang di chuyển chậm chạp, nhưng sự bò trườn này có thể gây ra <strong>hậu quả nghiêm trọng</strong> (<strong>serious consequences</strong>) nếu chúng đi vào đường ray xe lửa hoặc các lắp đặt dầu khí (industry/communications).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>28. Paragraph B</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: viii. The commonest type of dune</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn B tập trung vào loại đụn cát “linear” (tuyến tính) và nói rằng chúng chiếm <strong>hơn một nửa</strong> (“over half”) diện tích cát, biến chúng thành loại đụn cát phổ biến nhất (<strong>commonest type</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>29. Paragraph C</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: vi. Needing a specific combination of conditions</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn C nói về loại đụn cát “barchans” và giải thích rằng chúng <strong>“only tend to form where you have one-directional winds on the edge of sandy deserts near coastal areas”</strong>. Đây là một sự kết hợp các điều kiện cụ thể.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>30. Paragraph D</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: vii. A continuous cycle</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn D giải thích cơ chế di chuyển của đụn cát theo chu kỳ: hạt cát bị gió thổi lên lưng đụn, tích tụ lại, trượt xuống, bị chôn vùi, rồi lại xuất hiện ở phía sau để <strong>lặp lại quá trình</strong> (<strong>repeat the process</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>31. Paragraph E</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: v. Dunes coming together and re-forming</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn E mô tả cách các đụn cát <strong>tự điều chỉnh hình dạng</strong> (“regulate its own shape”) và “Even when <strong>two dunes collide, they quickly take on their distinctive shapes again</strong>.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>32. Paragraph F</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: ix. Old superstitions demystified</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn F bắt đầu bằng việc nhắc đến các <strong>huyền thoại địa phương</strong> (<strong>Local legends</strong>) gán tiếng hát của đụn cát cho các linh hồn nguy hiểm, sau đó nhà khoa học Douady đưa ra lời giải thích <strong>thực tế hơn</strong> (pragmatic) về âm thanh đó, tức là giải mã (demystified) các mê tín cũ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>33. Paragraph G</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: ii. Recreating the process in a laboratory</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn G mô tả cách các nhà khoa học lấy mẫu cát về Pháp và <strong>tái tạo lại âm thanh ở ENS</strong> (<strong>replicate the sound at ENS</strong>), chứng minh rằng họ có thể <strong>tái tạo</strong> quá trình này trong phòng thí nghiệm.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('11ef5dcc-eba9-42d4-9ad9-c92774bddbf8', '1f388ca3-a8a3-4e15-86cf-d0f35f570a4f', 'radio', 'Questions 37-40', '', NULL, 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "Yes"}, {"option_text": "No"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "Any sort of artificial general intelligence must have the capacity for metabolism and reproduction."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "Yes"}, {"option_text": "No"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "Intelligence may depend on the ability to interact with a complex and unpredictable environment."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "Yes"}, {"option_text": "No"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "It is dangerous to rely too much on multi-specialist robots which could develop unfixable faults."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Training by experts is essential for acquiring certain types of skills."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. Any sort of artificial general intelligence must have the capacity for metabolism and reproduction. — {NO}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“So while the endeavor to create artificial general intelligence might <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">succeed without much that is essential to biological life, such as metabolism and reproduction</strong>, perhaps embodiment is a methodological necessity.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả cho rằng nỗ lực tạo ra AI tổng quát có thể <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">thành công mà không cần</strong> đến những đặc tính sinh học như trao đổi chất (<em data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">metabolism</em>) hay sinh sản (<em data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">reproduction</em>). Câu hỏi nói rằng “nhất thiết phải có” (<em data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"214\">must have</em>) nên mâu thuẫn trực tiếp với bài đọc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Intelligence may depend on the ability to interact with a complex and unpredictable environment. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Perhaps the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">need to engage with a messy, dynamic, physical environment</strong> full of complex and varied objects… is at the root of intelligence.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả sử dụng các tính từ tương đương: “messy, dynamic” (hỗn độn, năng động) trong bài tương ứng với “complex and unpredictable” (phức tạp và không dự đoán được) trong câu hỏi. Tác giả khẳng định việc tương tác với môi trường như vậy có thể là cái gốc (<em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"267\">root</em>) của trí tuệ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. It is dangerous to rely too much on multi-specialist robots which could develop unfixable faults. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The multi-specialist robot is going to <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">get stuck</strong> as soon as it has to face a problem that is outside its areas of expertise…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả có nhắc đến việc robot đa chuyên môn sẽ “bị kẹt” (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">get stuck</em>) khi gặp vấn đề ngoài phạm vi chuyên môn, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">không hề đề cập</strong> đến việc chúng có “nguy hiểm” (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"175\">dangerous</em>) hay có “lỗi không thể sửa” (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"214\">unfixable faults</em>) hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. Training by experts is essential for acquiring certain types of skills. — {NO}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 9):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The hallmark of general intelligence in a robot is therefore the ability to adapt… and to do so <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"119\">without recourse to trial and error or to training by a third party</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả định nghĩa đặc điểm của trí tuệ tổng quát là khả năng tự thích nghi mà <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">không cần viện đến</strong> sự đào tạo từ bên thứ ba (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">training by a third party/experts</em>). Câu hỏi khẳng định sự đào tạo là “thiết yếu” (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"218\">essential</em>) nên trái ngược hoàn toàn với quan điểm của tác giả.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5b3307de-a95a-4b75-85cb-45b7eb0d15e2', 'fdfbb0e0-1209-4ede-a0f2-73bf7cb50bb1', 'radio', 'Questions 34–36', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A They are formed by strong winds blowing from one direction.  "}, {"content": "B They can move up to 100 metres in a twelve-month period  "}, {"content": "C They develop in a recognisable shape.  "}, {"content": "D They make up about 20% of the world''s deserts."}], "question": "What are we told about linear dunes?   "}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A the long straight shape of the dunes  "}, {"content": "B the particular composition of the dunes.  "}, {"content": "C the exceptionally heavy nature of the sand grains.  "}, {"content": "D the unusual strength of the wind in certain seasons."}], "question": "Bagnold discovered that movement in barchans was caused by   "}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A It starts small and then increases in size.  "}, {"content": "B It has an effect on its immediate surroundings.  "}, {"content": "C Its relations with desert organisms are quite developed  "}, {"content": "D Its outline stays the same even after a period of movement"}], "question": "Why does Dr Douady compare a barchan dune to a living organism?   "}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>34. What are we told about linear dunes?</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: C. They develop in a recognisable shape.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “These form in a <strong>long curving wave</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> “Long curving wave” là một hình dạng có thể nhận biết được (recognisable shape). (A, B, D là sai hoặc không đúng với linear dunes).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>35. Bagnold discovered that movement in barchans was caused by</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: B. the particular composition of the dunes.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “…his answer hinges on the fact that dunes aren’t solid, but <strong>granular</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cơ chế di chuyển dựa trên việc đụn cát bao gồm các <strong>hạt cát</strong> (granular) riêng lẻ di chuyển theo chu kỳ, đây là <strong>thành phần/cấu tạo</strong> (composition) vật chất của đụn cát.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>36. Why does Dr Douady compare a barchan dune to a living organism?</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: D. Its outline stays the same even after a period of movement.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “Interestingly, the dune can <strong>regulate its own shape, and maintain it as it moves</strong>… Even when two dunes collide, they quickly <strong>take on their distinctive shapes again</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đụn cát duy trì hình dáng đặc trưng (outline stays the same) mặc dù có di chuyển hay va chạm.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
SET session_replication_role = DEFAULT;
